In case of single-cos Flow index 1 represents shaper going to Network 1 port; index 9 represents shaper going to Network 2 port.

cmQosShaperDirection.name: cmQosShaperDirection
cmQosShaperDirection.description: The direction of the Quality of Service Shaper.

cmQosShaperAdminState.name: cmQosShaperAdminState
cmQosShaperAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the QOS Shaper.

cmQosShaperOperationalState.name: cmQosShaperOperationalState
cmQosShaperOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the QOS Shaper.

cmQosShaperSecondaryState.name: cmQosShaperSecondaryState
cmQosShaperSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the QOS Shaper.

cmQosShaperCIR.name: cmQosShaperCIR
cmQosShaperCIR.description: This object represents the Commited Information Rate(CIR) (Lower 32 bits)of a Shaper.

cmQosShaperCBS.name: cmQosShaperCBS
cmQosShaperCBS.description: This object represents the Commited Burst Size (CBS) of the Shaper.

cmQosShaperEIR.name: cmQosShaperEIR
cmQosShaperEIR.description: This object represents the Excess Information Rate(EIR) (Lower 32 bits) of a Shaper.

cmQosShaperEBS.name: cmQosShaperEBS
cmQosShaperEBS.description: This object represents the Excess Burst Size (EBS) of the Shaper.

cmQosShaperBufferSize.name: cmQosShaperBufferSize
cmQosShaperBufferSize.description: This object represents the Buffer Size of the Shaper.

cmQosShaperStorageType.name: cmQosShaperStorageType
cmQosShaperStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmQosShaperRowStatus.name: cmQosShaperRowStatus
cmQosShaperRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cmQosShaperRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with cmQosShaperRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cmQosShaperRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

cmQosShaperCOS.name: cmQosShaperCOS
cmQosShaperCOS.description: This object provides the COS (Class of Service) value for the QOS Shaper.

cmQosShaperCIRHi.name: cmQosShaperCIRHi
cmQosShaperCIRHi.description: This object represents the Commited Information Rate(CIR) (Higher 32 bits) of a Shaper.

cmQosShaperEIRHi.name: cmQosShaperEIRHi
cmQosShaperEIRHi.description: This object represents the Excess Information Rate(EIR) (Higher 32 bits) on the Shaper.

cmQosShaperSoamCIRLo.name: cmQosShaperSoamCIRLo
cmQosShaperSoamCIRLo.description: This object represents the Soam Commited Information Rate(SOAM-CIR) (Lower 32 bits) of a Shaper.

cmQosShaperSoamCIRHi.name: cmQosShaperSoamCIRHi
cmQosShaperSoamCIRHi.description: This object represents the Soam Commited Information Rate(SOAM-CIR) (Higher 32 bits) on the Shaper.

cmQosShaperSoamEIRLo.name: cmQosShaperSoamEIRLo
cmQosShaperSoamEIRLo.description: This object represents the Soam Excess Information Rate(SOAM-EIR) (Lower 32 bits) of a Shaper.

cmQosShaperSoamEIRHi.name: cmQosShaperSoamEIRHi
cmQosShaperSoamEIRHi.description: This object represents the Soam Excess Information Rate(SOAM-EIR) (Higher 32 bits) on the Shaper.

cmQosShaperWredGreenMinQueueThreshold.name: cmQosShaperWredGreenMinQueueThreshold
cmQosShaperWredGreenMinQueueThreshold.description: This object represents the Wred green packet min queue threshold value.

cmQosShaperWredGreenMaxQueueThreshold.name: cmQosShaperWredGreenMaxQueueThreshold
cmQosShaperWredGreenMaxQueueThreshold.description: This object represents the Wred green packet max queue threshold value.

cmQosShaperWredGreenDropProbability.name: cmQosShaperWredGreenDropProbability
cmQosShaperWredGreenDropProbability.description: This object represents the Wred green packet drop probability.

cmQosShaperWredYellowMinQueueThreshold.name: cmQosShaperWredYellowMinQueueThreshold
cmQosShaperWredYellowMinQueueThreshold.description: This object represents the Wred yellow packet min queue threshold value.

cmQosShaperWredYellowMaxQueueThreshold.name: cmQosShaperWredYellowMaxQueueThreshold
cmQosShaperWredYellowMaxQueueThreshold.description: This object represents the Wred yellow packet max queue threshold value.

cmQosShaperWredYellowDropProbability.name: cmQosShaperWredYellowDropProbability
cmQosShaperWredYellowDropProbability.description: This object represents the Wred yellow packet drop probability.

cmEthernetNetPortTable.name: cmEthernetNetPortTable
cmEthernetNetPortTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Network Port Facilities for configuration purposes.

cmEthernetNetPortEntry.name: cmEthernetNetPortEntry
cmEthernetNetPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetNetPortTable.

cmEthernetNetPortIndex.name: cmEthernetNetPortIndex
cmEthernetNetPortIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Ethernet Network Port within a card. Note that each Ethernet Network Port is uniquely identified by the indices neIndex, shelfIndex, slotIndex, cmEthernetNetPortIndex.

cmEthernetNetPortIfIndex.name: cmEthernetNetPortIfIndex
cmEthernetNetPortIfIndex.description: This object has the same value as ifIndex for Ethernet Network Port. An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortEntityIndex.name: cmEthernetNetPortEntityIndex
cmEthernetNetPortEntityIndex.description: Entity Index from ENTITY-MIB for this port.

cmEthernetNetPortAdminState.name: cmEthernetNetPortAdminState
cmEthernetNetPortAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortOperationalState.name: cmEthernetNetPortOperationalState
cmEthernetNetPortOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortSecondaryState.name: cmEthernetNetPortSecondaryState
cmEthernetNetPortSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortMTU.name: cmEthernetNetPortMTU
cmEthernetNetPortMTU.description: This object provides the MTU on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortMediaType.name: cmEthernetNetPortMediaType
cmEthernetNetPortMediaType.description: This object represents the type of Ethernet Media on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortConfigSpeed.name: cmEthernetNetPortConfigSpeed
cmEthernetNetPortConfigSpeed.description: This object allows to configure the speed of the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortNegotiatedSpeed.name: cmEthernetNetPortNegotiatedSpeed
cmEthernetNetPortNegotiatedSpeed.description: This object provides the negotiated speed of the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortMDIXType.name: cmEthernetNetPortMDIXType
cmEthernetNetPortMDIXType.description: This object allows management of MDIX property on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortJumboFramesEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortJumboFramesEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortJumboFramesEnabled.description: This object allows enabling/disabling jumbo frames support on the Ethernet Network Port. This object is only applicable for Ethernet Network Port on R3.1CM NTU Card.

cmEthernetNetPortSfpVendorName.name: cmEthernetNetPortSfpVendorName
cmEthernetNetPortSfpVendorName.description: This object provides the vendor name of the SFP. This is applicable when cmEthernetNetPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetNetPortSfpPartNumber.name: cmEthernetNetPortSfpPartNumber
cmEthernetNetPortSfpPartNumber.description: This object provides the part number of the SFP. This is applicable when cmEthernetNetPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetNetPortSfpSerialNumber.name: cmEthernetNetPortSfpSerialNumber
cmEthernetNetPortSfpSerialNumber.description: This object provides the serial number of the SFP. This is applicable when cmEthernetNetPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetNetPortSfpDateOfManufacture.name: cmEthernetNetPortSfpDateOfManufacture
cmEthernetNetPortSfpDateOfManufacture.description: This object provides the date of manufacture of the SFP. This is applicable when cmEthernetNetPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetNetPortSfpConnectorValue.name: cmEthernetNetPortSfpConnectorValue
cmEthernetNetPortSfpConnectorValue.description: This object provides the SFP connector value. This is applicable when cmEthernetNetPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetNetPortInitiateDiag.name: cmEthernetNetPortInitiateDiag
cmEthernetNetPortInitiateDiag.description: This object allows to initiate Etherjack diagnosis on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair1Cond.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair1Cond
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair1Cond.description: This object provides diagnosis results for the cable Pair 1 on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair2Cond.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair2Cond
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair2Cond.description: This object provides diagnosis results for the cable Pair 2 on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair3Cond.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair3Cond
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair3Cond.description: This object provides diagnosis results for the cable Pair 3 on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair4Cond.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair4Cond
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosePair4Cond.description: This object provides diagnosis results for the cable Pair 4 on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseAutoNegCond.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseAutoNegCond
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseAutoNegCond.description: This object provides auto negotiation results of the diagnosis test on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseLpbkCond.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseLpbkCond
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseLpbkCond.description: This object provides port loopback results of the diagnosis test on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseEfmLpbkCond.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseEfmLpbkCond
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseEfmLpbkCond.description: This object provides remote EFM loopback results of the diagnosis test on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseResult.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseResult
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseResult.description: This object provides results of the diagnosis test in string form on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseTestStatus.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseTestStatus
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseTestStatus.description: This object provides the current status of the diagnosis test on Ethernet Access Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseTestTime.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseTestTime
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnoseTestTime.description: This object provides the time when diagnosis test was last executed.

cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackConfig.name: cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackConfig
cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackConfig.description: This object allows to initiate loopbacks on on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackStatus.name: cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackStatus
cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackStatus.description: This object provides status of the current loopback on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackTime.name: cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackTime
cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackTime.description: This object allows to specify time for timed-loopbacks on on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackSwapSADA.name: cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackSwapSADA
cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackSwapSADA.description: This object allows to specify whether or not the loopbacked frame will have the Source Address and Destination Address swapped.

cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask.name: cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask
cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask.description: This object allows specification of the outer VLANs to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. Only 3 VLANs can be specified for vlan loopback. The various bit positions are: 1 Outer VLAN 1 Loopback Enabled 2 Outer VLAN 2 Loopback Enabled 4 Outer VLAN 3 Loopback Enabled Value of 0 means that no VLANs are enabled.

cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopback1.name: cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopback1
cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopback1.description: This object allows specification of the outer VLAN 1 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopback2.name: cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopback2
cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopback2.description: This object allows specification of the outer VLAN 2 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopback3.name: cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopback3
cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopback3.description: This object allows specification of the outer VLAN 3 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetNetPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask.name: cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask
cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask.description: This object allows specification of the inner VLANs to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. Only 3 VLANs can be specified for vlan loopback. The various bit positions are: 1 Inner VLAN 1 Loopback Enabled 2 Inner VLAN 2 Loopback Enabled 4 Inner VLAN 3 Loopback Enabled Value of 0 means that no VLANs are enabled.

cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopback1.name: cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopback1
cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopback1.description: This object allows specification of the inner VLAN 1 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopback2.name: cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopback2
cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopback2.description: This object allows specification of the inner VLAN 2 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopback3.name: cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopback3
cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopback3.description: This object allows specification of the inner VLAN 3 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetNetPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdEnabled.description: This object allows enabling/disabling link loss forwarding on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdSignalType.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdSignalType
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdSignalType.description: This object allows definition of the link loss forwarding signalling type. This is applicable only if cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdEnabled is enabled. This object is only valid for FSP150CM Release 3.1. This object is deprecated henceforth. Link Loss signalling will be supported using the object cmEthernetAccPortLinkLossFwdTxActionType.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdTriggerTypes.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdTriggerTypes
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdTriggerTypes.description: This object allows definition of the link loss forwarding trigger types. This is applicable only if cmEthernetAccPortLinkLossFwdEnabled is enabled.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdDelay.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdDelay
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdDelay.description: This object allows specification of the delay between detection of link loss and signalling of link loss forwarding. Time specified is in seconds.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdActive.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdActive
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdActive.description: This object provides the link loss forwarding status indicating if link loss forwarding is currently being signaled via the port.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdPartnerEnabl.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdPartnerEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdPartnerEnabl.description: This object provides the indication of a link partners ability to support link loss forwarding via EFM, i.e. from received organization specific OAMPDUs.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdLocalLinkId.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdLocalLinkId
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdLocalLinkId.description: This object allows configuration of the Local Link Id on Ethernet Network port.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdRemoteLinkId.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdRemoteLinkIds
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdRemoteLinkId.description: This object allows enabling/disabling Remote Link Ids on Ethernet Network port. By setting the appropriate bit positions, the Ethernet Network port is able to distinguish the remote side client ports from the Remote Link Down PDUs coming from remote end.

cmEthernetNetPortOamId.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamId
cmEthernetNetPortOamId.description: OAM Id. This is unique EFM OAM sublayer port id.

cmEthernetNetPortOamAdminDisposition.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamAdminDisposition
cmEthernetNetPortOamAdminDisposition.description: Ethernet Network Port's EFM OAM Administrative Disposition. This object is applicable only for FSP150CM Release 3.1. This object is deprecated henceforth. With FSP150CC Release 4.1, this property is managed using the Control Protocol Disposition tables.

cmEthernetNetPortOamDiscoveryState.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamDiscoveryState
cmEthernetNetPortOamDiscoveryState.description: Ethernet Network Port's OAM discovery state.

cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalVarRtrvsEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalVarRtrvsEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalVarRtrvsEnabled.description: This object allows specification of whether the Ethernet Network Port supports sending variable response OAMPDUs.

cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalLinkEventsEnabl.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalLinkEventsEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalLinkEventsEnabl.description: This object allows specification of whether the Ethernet Network Port supports interpreting Link Events.

cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalOamLoopbacksSup.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalOamLoopbacksSupported
cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalOamLoopbacksSup.description: This object allows specification of whether the Ethernet Network Port is capable of OAM remote loopback mode.

cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalUnidirSupportEn.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalUnidirSupportEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalUnidirSupportEn.description: This object allows specification of whether the Ethernet Network Port is capable of sending OAMPDUs when the receive path is non-operational.

cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalMaxPDUSize.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalMaxPDUSize
cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalMaxPDUSize.description: This object represents the largest OAMPDU, in octets, supported by the Ethernet Network Port. This value is compared to the remote Maximum PDU Size and the smaller of the two is used.

cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalMode.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalMode
cmEthernetNetPortOamLocalMode.description: This object allows to configure the OAM sublayer entity in either Active or Passive mode.

cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteMacAddress.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteMacAddress
cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteMacAddress.description: This object allows retrieval of the Remote Mac Address.

cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteVarRtrvsEnable.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteVarRtrvsEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteVarRtrvsEnable.description: This object allows retrieval of whether the remote OAM entity supports sending variable response OAMPDUs.

cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteLinkEventsEnab.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteLinkEventsEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteLinkEventsEnab.description: This object allows retrieval of whether the remote OAM entity supports interpreting Link Events.

cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteOamLoopbacksSu.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteOamLoopbacksSupported
cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteOamLoopbacksSu.description: This object allows retrieval of whether the remote OAM entity supports OAM remote loopback mode.

cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteUnidirSupportE.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteUnidirSupportEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteUnidirSupportE.description: This object allows retrieval of whether the remote OAM entity is capable of sending OAMPDUs when the receive path is non-operational.

cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteMaxPDUSize.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteMaxPDUSize
cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteMaxPDUSize.description: This object allows retrieval of the remote OAM entity maximum OAMPDU size.

cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteMode.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteMode
cmEthernetNetPortOamRemoteMode.description: This object allows to retrieve whether the remote OAM sublayer entity is either in Active or Passive mode.

cmEthernetNetPortRxPauseDisposition.name: cmEthernetNetPortRxPauseDisposition
cmEthernetNetPortRxPauseDisposition.description: This object allows enabling/disabling receive pause frames on Ethernet Network port. This object is not applicable for FSP150CC Release 4.1 products.

cmEthernetNetPortTxPauseEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortTxPauseEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortTxPauseEnabled.description: This object allows enabling/disabling transmit pause frames on Ethernet Network port. This object is not applicable for FSP150CC Release 4.1 products.

cmEthernetNetPortAfpType.name: cmEthernetNetPortAfpType
cmEthernetNetPortAfpType.description: This object allows specification of the Acceptable Frame Policy on Ethernet Network port. Users can specify whether the port supports only tagged frames, only untagged frames or both tagged and untagged frames. This object is not applicable for FSP150CC Release 4.1 products.

cmEthernetNetPortMDIXStatus.name: cmEthernetNetPortMDIXStatus
cmEthernetNetPortMDIXStatus.description: This object provides the current MDIX status of the Ethernet Network port.

cmEthernetNetPortSfpReach.name: cmEthernetNetPortSfpReach
cmEthernetNetPortSfpReach.description: This object provides the SFP Reach in meters. This is applicable when cmEthernetNetPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetNetPortSfpLaserWaveLength.name: cmEthernetNetPortSfpLaserWaveLength
cmEthernetNetPortSfpLaserWaveLength.description: This object provides the SFP Laser Wave Length in nano meters. This is applicable only when cmEthernetNetPortMediaType is fiber.

cmEthernetNetPortSfpMediaType.name: cmEthernetNetPortSfpMediaType
cmEthernetNetPortSfpMediaType.description: This object provides the SFP Media Type. This is applicable when cmEthernetNetPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetNetPortOamEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortOamEnabled.description: This object allows to manage the EFM OAM on Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortOamAdminState.name: cmEthernetNetPortOamAdminState
cmEthernetNetPortOamAdminState.description: This object provides the EFM OAM Admin State.

cmEthernetNetPortShapingEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortShapingEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortShapingEnabled.description: This object allows to manage the Network Port Shaping. When enabled, values in cmEthernetNetPortShapedSpeedLo and cmEthernetNetPortShapedSpeedHi are applicable.

cmEthernetNetPortShapedSpeedLo.name: cmEthernetNetPortShapedSpeedLo
cmEthernetNetPortShapedSpeedLo.description: This object allows to specify the lower 32 bits of the Network Port Shaped speed. This value is applicable when cmEthernetNetPortShapingEnabled is enabled.

cmEthernetNetPortShapedSpeedHi.name: cmEthernetNetPortShapedSpeedHi
cmEthernetNetPortShapedSpeedHi.description: This object allows to specify the higher 32 bits of the Network Port Shaped speed. This value is applicable when cmEthernetNetPortShapingEnabled is enabled.

cmEthernetNetPortQinQEtherType.name: cmEthernetNetPortQinQEtherType
cmEthernetNetPortQinQEtherType.description: This object allows to specify the Q-in-Q Ether Type on the Network Port. Setting this value to 0 will disable the Q-in-Q override on the Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdTxActionType.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdTxActionType
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdTxActionType.description: This object allows to specify the Network Port's behavior when link loss forwarding trigger events occur on the Access Port.

cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdRxRLDLinkIds.name: cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdRxRLDLinkIds
cmEthernetNetPortLinkLossFwdRxRLDLinkIds.description: This object provides the received Remote Link IDs in EFM RLD messages on the Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortAutoDiagEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortAutoDiagEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortAutoDiagEnabled.description: This object allows to enable or disable the automatic Cable Diagnostic tests when the cable is removed from the port.

cmEthernetNetPortSyncEEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortSyncEEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortSyncEEnabled.description: This object allows to specify whether the Ethernet Network Port can be enabled/disabled for Synchronous Ethernet. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports. When enabled, on receive side -port can extract the frequency of its input signal and pass the recovered clock to the system clock -port processes the ESMC(Ethernet Synchronization Messaging Channel) and extracts the QL (when also QL enabled) -port is eligible to be selected as a system clock reference When enabled, on transmit side -port's transmit clock is locked to the system clock -port generates an ESMC to generate a QL (when also QL enabled) When disabled, on receive side, -port does not pass the recovered clock to the system clock -port does not process the ESMC (if present) -port is not eligible to be selected as a system clock reference When disabled, on transmit side -port's output frequency may be synchronized to the system clock -port does not generate an ESMC.

cmEthernetNetPortQLModeEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortQLModeEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortQLModeEnabled.description: This object allows to specify whether the Ethernet Network Port can be enabled/disabled for QL Mode. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports, when cmEthernetNetPortQLModeEnabled is set to true. When enabled, on receive side -port shall PEER the SSM (Sync Status Messages) slow protocol PDUs and take appropriate action When enabled, on transmit side -port shall periodically (once a second) transmit QL TLV information PDUs When disabled, on receive side, -port shall terminate and discard any SSM slow protocol PDUs When disabled, on transmit side -port shall not transmit any SSM slow protocol PDUs.

cmEthernetNetPortExpectedQL.name: cmEthernetNetPortExpectedQL
cmEthernetNetPortExpectedQL.description: This object allows to specify the expected QL when the Ethernet Network Port is enabled for QL Mode. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports, when cmEthernetNetPortQLModeEnabled is set to true. This object allows the user to set a minimum expected received Quality Level on the port. The valid values depend upon the SYNC entity's Network Clock Type. A value of None represents that a minimum Quality Level is not expected. The default value shall be None.

cmEthernetNetPortAssumedQL.name: cmEthernetNetPortAssumedQL
cmEthernetNetPortAssumedQL.description: This object allows to specify the assumed QL on the Ethernet Network Port. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports. The Assumed QL is only meaningful if the Network Clock Type (see fsp150cm-sync.mib) is option1 and the port's QL Mode is disabled and the port is being used as an input reference source. Under these conditions, the specified QL value is assumed to be the Quality Level of the non-failed reference.

cmEthernetNetPortReceivedQL.name: cmEthernetNetPortReceivedQL
cmEthernetNetPortReceivedQL.description: This object provides the Received QL value for the Ethernet port. If the Ethernet port's QL Mode is disabled, then the received QL value is not applicable.This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports.

cmEthernetNetPortTransmitQL.name: cmEthernetNetPortTransmitQL
cmEthernetNetPortTransmitQL.description: This object provides the Transmitted QL value for the Ethernet port. If the Ethernet port's QL Mode is disabled, then the received QL value is not applicable. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports.

cmEthernetNetPortPrioMapMode.name: cmEthernetNetPortPrioMapMode
cmEthernetNetPortPrioMapMode.description: This object provides the Priority Mapping Mode used for classification of frames.

cmEthernetNetPortDeiEnable.name: cmEthernetNetPortDeiEnable
cmEthernetNetPortDeiEnable.description: This is a port level control to reset the DEI (Drop Eligibility Indicator) bit in the S-Tag, if the downstream equipment supports S-Tag TPID (EtherType) but cannot handle DEI bit set. In the receive direction, it uses the S-TAG DEI when enabled, else ignores it. The following comment is NOT relevant to OSA8.1.1, since this object is still supported by OSA8.1.1. The object has been deprecated. The respective configuration should be managed by following objects: cmEthernetNetPortRxDeiAction, cmEthernetNetPortTxDeiAction, cmEthernetNetPortRxDeiOuterTagType, cmEthernetNetPortTxDeiOuterTagType.

cmEthernetNetPortPcpDEEncType.name: cmEthernetNetPortPcpDEEncType
cmEthernetNetPortPcpDEEncType.description: This is a port level control that specifies the mode of drop eligibility encoding in PCP bits of the VLAN tag.

cmEthernetNetPortPcpDEPairsAction.name: cmEthernetNetPortPcpDEPairsAction
cmEthernetNetPortPcpDEPairsAction.description: This object allows the SNMP user to manage the Priority Code Point (PCP) Drop Eligibility Pairs. When the cmEthernetNetPortPcpDEEncType is of type 7p1d, 6p2d, 5p3d, the cmNetPortPcpDEPairTable can be used to specify alternate pairs of priorities to specify drop eligibility/ ineligibility.

cmEthernetNetPortSSMRemoteMacAddress.name: cmEthernetNetPortSSMRemoteMacAddress
cmEthernetNetPortSSMRemoteMacAddress.description: This object allows retrieval of the Remote Mac Address, when the port is peering using SSM.

cmEthernetNetPortXgePhyType.name: cmEthernetNetPortXgePhyType
cmEthernetNetPortXgePhyType.description: This object allows to specify the PHY type of 10G Ethernet Port. 10G ports can operate in LAN-PHY or WAN-PHY mode. The default mode is LAN-PHY and port rate in this mode is 10Gbps. In WAN-PHY mode the port rate is 9.29Gbps. This attribute is only applicable for ports configured to work at speed-10G-full. For other speeds the value of this object must be 'not-applicable' and cannot be changed.

cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackSourceMacContro.name: cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackSourceMacControlEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackSourceMacContro.description: This object allows to Enable/Disable the Net Port Source MAC Address frame matching criteria for all streams. Not applicable for: efm-oam-remote, efm-oam-remote-timed.

cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackDestMacControlE.name: cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackDestMacControlEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackDestMacControlE.description: This object allows to Enable/Disable the Net Port Destination MAC Address frame matching criteria for all streams. Not applicable for: efm-oam-remote, efm-oam-remote-timed.

cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackSourceMacAddres.name: cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackSourceMacAddress
cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackSourceMacAddres.description: This object allows to set Net Port Source MAC Address for frame matching when Net Port Source MAC Control is enabled.

cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackDestMacAddress.name: cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackDestMacAddress
cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackDestMacAddress.description: This object allows to set Net Port Destination MAC Address for frame matching when Net Port Destination MAC Control is enabled.

cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackBlockingEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackBlockingEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortLoopbackBlockingEnabled.description: This object allows frame blocking when loopback is active. - True: Blocks frames in the non-loopback direction that match the PORT or VLAN received in the non-loopback direction. Discards frames in the loopback direction that match the PORT or VLAN, but do not match the MAC address criteria, - False: No blocking of frames.

cmEthernetNetPortRxDeiAction.name: cmEthernetNetPortRxDeiAction
cmEthernetNetPortRxDeiAction.description: This object allows to specify the Receive DEI Action.

cmEthernetNetPortTxDeiAction.name: cmEthernetNetPortTxDeiAction
cmEthernetNetPortTxDeiAction.description: This object allows to specify the Transmit DEI Action.

cmEthernetNetPortRxDeiOuterTagType.name: cmEthernetNetPortRxDeiOuterTagType
cmEthernetNetPortRxDeiOuterTagType.description: This object allows to specify the Receive DEI Outer Tag Type.

cmEthernetNetPortTxDeiOuterTagType.name: cmEthernetNetPortTxDeiOuterTagType
cmEthernetNetPortTxDeiOuterTagType.description: This object allows to specify the Transmit DEI Outer Tag Type.

cmEthernetNetPortLaserWDMChannel.name: cmEthernetNetPortLaserWDMChannel
cmEthernetNetPortLaserWDMChannel.description: Channel number of WDM tunable XFP setting.

cmEthernetNetPortLaserIsTunable.name: cmEthernetNetPortLaserIsTunable
cmEthernetNetPortLaserIsTunable.description: Channel number of WDM tunable XFP setting.

cmEthernetNetPortLaserFrequency.name: cmEthernetNetPortLaserFrequency
cmEthernetNetPortLaserFrequency.description: Channel number of WDM tunable XFP setting.

cmEthernetNetPortMediaTypeAutoSelected.name: cmEthernetNetPortMediaTypeAutoSelected
cmEthernetNetPortMediaTypeAutoSelected.description: This object provides the auto selected Ethernet Media of the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortLowLatencyQueuingEnable.name: cmEthernetNetPortLowLatencyQueuingEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortLowLatencyQueuingEnable.description: This object allows to Enable/Disable the Low Latency Queuing on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosticMacAddress.name: cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosticMacAddress
cmEthernetNetPortDiagnosticMacAddress.description: This object describes the diagnose mac address for SAT, ECPA, JDSU, Loopback with Override SA etc.

cmEthernetNetPortIngressCOSPriority.name: cmEthernetNetPortIngressCOSPriority
cmEthernetNetPortIngressCOSPriority.description: Indicates the VLAN tag to use for PCP Priority to COS mapping when the port Priority Map Mode is 802.1p. Supported values are inner-vlantag and outer-vlantag. This attribute is only applicable on products when Flowpoint Model is supported. inner-vlantag: The inner VLAN tag PCP Priority of a frame is used for ingress COS mapping. A frame with no inner VLAN tag (untagged or single-tagged) will have a COS equal to the default COS of the port. outer-vlantag: The outer VLAN tag PCP Priority of a frame is used for ingress COS mapping. A frame with no outer VLAN tag (untagged) will have a COS equal to the default COS of the port. This attribute has been deprecated and is not supported. Now, the Priority Map Mode indicates whether it is inner or outer. Use priomap-8021p(4) for outer and priomap-8021p-inner(5) for inner.

cmEthernetNetPortDefaultCOS.name: cmEthernetNetPortDefaultCOS
cmEthernetNetPortDefaultCOS.description: The COS assigned to a frame that does not have a valid COS identifier for the Priority Map Mode of the port. This attribute is only applicable on products when Flowpoint Model is supported. This value is assigned to a frame received on a port when: - the cmEthernetNetPortPrioMapMode=priomap-8021p, ingressCOSPriority=inner-vlantag; and the frame is untagged - the cmEthernetNetPortPrioMapMode=priomap-8021p, ingressCOSPriority=inner-vlantag; and the frame has a single VLAN tag - the cmEthernetNetPortPrioMapMode=priomap-8021p, ingressCOSPriority=outer-vlantag; and the frame is untagged - the cmEthernetNetPortPrioMapMode=priomap-dscp; and the frame does not have an IP ethertype - the cmEthernetNetPortPrioMapMode=priomap-tos; and the frame does not have an IP ethertype. This attribute has been deprecated and is not supported. The Default COS is determined from the flowpoint's associated Priority Mapping Profle.

cmEthernetNetPortTrafficModel.name: cmEthernetNetPortTrafficModel
cmEthernetNetPortTrafficModel.description: The Traffic Management connection model available for the port. - accessFlow: NID Traffic Connection model. - flowpoint: Multipoint and Aggregation Traffic Connection model.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdTable.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdTable
cmEthernetNetPortCpdTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Network Port Control Protocol Disposition. This table is only applicable for FSP150CM Hub Shelf Release 3.x.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdEntry.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdEntry
cmEthernetNetPortCpdEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetNetPortCpdTable. These entries represent a Control Protocol Disposition filtering criteria on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdIndex.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdIndex
cmEthernetNetPortCpdIndex.description: An arbitrary integer index value used to uniquely identify this CPD Service Entry.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdFilterType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdFilterType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdFilterType.description: This enables specification of type of CPD Filter.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdFilterDescr.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdFilterDescr
cmEthernetNetPortCpdFilterDescr.description: This provides description of CPD Filter.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdDispType.description: This enables specification of disposion type of CPD Filter.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdMacAddressMatch.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdMacAddressMatch
cmEthernetNetPortCpdMacAddressMatch.description: This enables provides the Filter MAC Address to match.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdMacAddressMask.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdMacAddressMask
cmEthernetNetPortCpdMacAddressMask.description: This enables provides the Filter MAC Address Mask to match.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdEthertype.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdEthertype
cmEthernetNetPortCpdEthertype.description: This enables provides the Filter Ethertype to match.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdEthertypeMask.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdEthertypeMask
cmEthernetNetPortCpdEthertypeMask.description: This enables provides the Filter Ethertype Mask to match.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdSubtype.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdSubtype
cmEthernetNetPortCpdSubtype.description: This enables provides the Filter Subtype to match.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdSubtypeMask.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdSubtypeMask
cmEthernetNetPortCpdSubtypeMask.description: This enables provides the Filter Subtype Mask to match.

cmEthernetMgmtPortTable.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortTable
cmEthernetMgmtPortTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Management Port Facilities for configuration purposes.

cmEthernetMgmtPortEntry.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortEntry
cmEthernetMgmtPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetMgmtPortTable.

cmEthernetMgmtPortIndex.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortIndex
cmEthernetMgmtPortIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Ethernet Management Port within a card. Note that each Ethernet Management Port is uniquely identified by the indices neIndex, shelfIndex, slotIndex, cmEthernetMgmtPortIndex.

cmEthernetMgmtPortEntityIndex.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortEntityIndex
cmEthernetMgmtPortEntityIndex.description: Entity Index from ENTITY-MIB for this port.

cmEthernetMgmtPortAdminState.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortAdminState
cmEthernetMgmtPortAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Ethernet Management Port.

cmEthernetMgmtPortOperationalState.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortOperationalState
cmEthernetMgmtPortOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Ethernet Management Port.

cmEthernetMgmtPortSecondaryState.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortSecondaryState
cmEthernetMgmtPortSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the Ethernet Management Port.

cmEthernetMgmtPortMTU.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortMTU
cmEthernetMgmtPortMTU.description: This object provides the MTU on the Ethernet Management Port.

cmEthernetMgmtPortConfigSpeed.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortConfigSpeed
cmEthernetMgmtPortConfigSpeed.description: This object allows to configure the speed of the Ethernet Management Port.

cmEthernetMgmtPortNegotiatedSpeed.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortNegotiatedSpeed
cmEthernetMgmtPortNegotiatedSpeed.description: This object provides the negotiated speed of the Ethernet Management Port.

cmEthernetMgmtPortMDIXType.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortMDIXType
cmEthernetMgmtPortMDIXType.description: This object allows management of MDIX property on Ethernet Management Port.

cmEthernetMgmtPortMDIXStatus.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortMDIXStatus
cmEthernetMgmtPortMDIXStatus.description: This object provides the current MDIX status of the Ethernet Management port.

cmEthernetMgmtPortMediaType.name: cmEthernetMgmtPortMediaType
cmEthernetMgmtPortMediaType.description: This object represents the type of Ethernet Media on the Ethernet Management Port.

cmPrioMapTable.name: cmPrioMapTable
cmPrioMapTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Priority Mappings in multi Class of Service (COS) mode. This table is applicable only when the Access Port is in connection-oriented evpl mode.

cmPrioMapEntry.name: cmPrioMapEntry
cmPrioMapEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmPrioMapTable.

cmPrioMapIndex.name: cmPrioMapIndex
cmPrioMapIndex.description: The integer index value corresponding to a priority value based on the cmEthernetAccPortPrioMapMode. In case of TOS and 8021P, valid indices are 1 to 8, in case of DSCP, valid indices are 1 to 64.

cmPrioMapInPriority.name: cmPrioMapInPriority
cmPrioMapInPriority.description: The integer index value corresponding to a priority value based on the cmEthernetAccPortPrioMapMode. In case of TOS and 8021P, valid indices are 0 to 7, in case of DSCP, valid indices are 0 to 63.

cmPrioMapXTagControl.name: cmPrioMapXTagControl
cmPrioMapXTagControl.description: This allows specification of whether the priority of incoming X-TAG should be swapped with cmPrioMapXTagPriority.

cmPrioMapXTagPriority.name: cmPrioMapXTagPriority
cmPrioMapXTagPriority.description: This allows specification of the VLAN priority that will replace the incoming X-TAG's priority. This is applicable with cmPrioMapXTagControl as 'swap'.

cmPrioMapCOS.name: cmPrioMapCOS
cmPrioMapCOS.description: This allows specification of the COS Priority, i.e. this helps in determining the appropriate COS Policer for the Flow.

cmPrioMapOuterTagPriority.name: cmPrioMapOuterTagPriority
cmPrioMapOuterTagPriority.description: This allows specification of the VLAN priority that will replace the outgoing (A2N direction) outer-tag's priority. Note that, each flow participates or not in outer-tag priority mapping, using the object 'cmFlowOuterTagPrioEnabled'.

cmPrioMapInnerTagPriority.name: cmPrioMapInnerTagPriority
cmPrioMapInnerTagPriority.description: This allows specification of the VLAN priority that will replace the outgoing (A2N direction) inner-tag's (i.e. second tag) priority. Note that, each flow participates or not in inner-tag priority mapping, using the object 'cmFlowInnerTagPrioEnabled'.

cmQosFlowPolicerTable.name: cmQosFlowPolicerTable
cmQosFlowPolicerTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Quality of Service Policer for configuration purposes.

cmQosFlowPolicerEntry.name: cmQosFlowPolicerEntry
cmQosFlowPolicerEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmQosFlowPolicerTable. These entries represent a Quality of Service Policer.

cmQosFlowPolicerTypeIndex.name: cmQosFlowPolicerTypeIndex
cmQosFlowPolicerTypeIndex.description: The unique index value corresponding to a Quality of Service Policer's direction. Values 1 and 2 are applicable to the Access Flow Policer - value of 1 stands for A2N direction, - value of 2 stands for N2A direction. Values 3 and 4 are applicable to Pass-thru Flow Policer (new in 5.6CC release): - value of 3 stands for N1toN2 direction - value of 4 stands for N2toN1 direction

cmQosFlowPolicerIndex.name: cmQosFlowPolicerIndex
cmQosFlowPolicerIndex.description: The Policer Index that represents the COS level. This is applicable in case of a Multi COS flow. Index 1 represents COS 0; Index 2 represents COS 1 and so on. In release 5.6CC the range is extended to 1..16 to support duplicate N2A policers on a Flow. The duplicate policers are created under a Flow if network interface of the Flow is ERP Group or Split Horizon Group. In case of multi-cos Flow indices 1..8 represent policers of COS 0..7 going from Network 1 port; indices 9..16 represent policers for COS 0..7 going from Network 2 port. In case of single-cos Flow index 1 represents policer going from Network 1 port; index 9 represents policer going from Network 2 port.

cmQosFlowPolicerDirection.name: cmQosFlowPolicerDirection
cmQosFlowPolicerDirection.description: This object is allows specification of Policer direction as 'a2n' or 'n2a'.

cmQosFlowPolicerAdminState.name: cmQosFlowPolicerAdminState
cmQosFlowPolicerAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the QOS Flow Policer.

cmQosFlowPolicerOperationalState.name: cmQosFlowPolicerOperationalState
cmQosFlowPolicerOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the QOS Flow Policer.

cmQosFlowPolicerSecondaryState.name: cmQosFlowPolicerSecondaryState
cmQosFlowPolicerSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the QOS Flow Policer.

cmQosFlowPolicerCIRLo.name: cmQosFlowPolicerCIRLo
cmQosFlowPolicerCIRLo.description: This object allows specification of the Commited Information Rate(CIR) on Policer. This represents the lower 32 bits of the CIR.

cmQosFlowPolicerCIRHi.name: cmQosFlowPolicerCIRHi
cmQosFlowPolicerCIRHi.description: This object allows specification of the Commited Information Rate(CIR) on Policer. This represents the upper 32 bits of the CIR.

cmQosFlowPolicerEIRLo.name: cmQosFlowPolicerEIRLo
cmQosFlowPolicerEIRLo.description: This object allows specification of the Excess Information Rate(EIR) on the Policer. This represents the lower 32 bits of the EIR.

cmQosFlowPolicerEIRHi.name: cmQosFlowPolicerEIRHi
cmQosFlowPolicerEIRHi.description: This object allows specification of the Excess Information Rate(EIR) on the Policer. This represents the upper 32 bits of the EIR.

cmQosFlowPolicerCBS.name: cmQosFlowPolicerCBS
cmQosFlowPolicerCBS.description: This object allows specification of the Commited Burst Size (CBS) on Policer.

cmQosFlowPolicerEBS.name: cmQosFlowPolicerEBS
cmQosFlowPolicerEBS.description: This object allows specification of the Excess Burst Size (EBS) on the Policer.

cmQosFlowPolicerAlgorithm.name: cmQosFlowPolicerAlgorithm
cmQosFlowPolicerAlgorithm.description: This object allows specification of Policer algorithm as 'srTCM' (Single Rate Triple Color Marking) or 'trTCM' (Two Rate Triple Color Marking).

cmQosFlowPolicerColorMode.name: cmQosFlowPolicerColorMode
cmQosFlowPolicerColorMode.description: This object allows specification of Policer Color Mode as 'color-aware' or 'color-blind'.

cmQosFlowPolicerColorMarkingFlag.name: cmQosFlowPolicerColorMarkingFlag
cmQosFlowPolicerColorMarkingFlag.description: This object allows specification of Policer Color Marking Flag. The policer will set/clear the DEI (Drop Eligibility Indication) bit of the frame on an S-TAG if this flag is enabled. This object is not supported - setting any value will not have effect on the System.

cmQosFlowPolicerCouplingFlag.name: cmQosFlowPolicerCouplingFlag
cmQosFlowPolicerCouplingFlag.description: This object allows specification of Policer Coupling Flag. When coupling is enabled, tokens that would normally be added to the C-bucket are passed to the E-bucket only once the CIR bucket has reached its CBS level. Therefore under this condition the E-bucket is being filled at the rate of CIR + EIR. Normally the long term average of frames declared yellow is bounded by the EIR. Coupling is a function to allow the long term average of frames declared yellow to be bounded by CIR + EIR. This allows a higher volume of yellow frames to be delivered/received if the arrival of green marked frames is low. Tokens from the E-bucket do NOT get passed to the C-bucket once the EBS level has been reached. Enabling coupling in combination with a provisioned EIR of 0 allows for a single rate three color marking (srTCM) algorithm to be established. In this situation the E-bucket is filled at the CIR rate in the case the C-bucket is filled to its CBS level.

cmQosFlowPolicerAssociatedShaper.name: cmQosFlowPolicerAssociatedShaper
cmQosFlowPolicerAssociatedShaper.description: This object allows specification of the QOS Shaper associated with this Policer. Multiple Policers can map to single Shaper. The corresponding row with the specified QOS value must exist in cmQosShaperTable when this value is specified.

cmQosFlowPolicerStorageType.name: cmQosFlowPolicerStorageType
cmQosFlowPolicerStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmQosFlowPolicerRowStatus.name: cmQosFlowPolicerRowStatus
cmQosFlowPolicerRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cmQosFlowPolicerRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with cmQosFlowPolicerRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cmQosFlowPolicerRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

cmAccPortQosShaperTable.name: cmAccPortQosShaperTable
cmAccPortQosShaperTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Access Port Quality of Service Shaper for configuration purposes. These shapers can be managed when the Access Port is in evpl mode and are relevant for traffic in the network to access direction.

cmAccPortQosShaperEntry.name: cmAccPortQosShaperEntry
cmAccPortQosShaperEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmAccPortQosShaperTable. These entries represent a Quality of Service Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperIndex.name: cmAccPortQosShaperIndex
cmAccPortQosShaperIndex.description: The unique integer index value corresponding to a Quality of Service Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperDirection.name: cmAccPortQosShaperDirection
cmAccPortQosShaperDirection.description: The direction of the Quality of Service Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperAdminState.name: cmAccPortQosShaperAdminState
cmAccPortQosShaperAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the QOS Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperOperationalState.name: cmAccPortQosShaperOperationalState
cmAccPortQosShaperOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the QOS Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperSecondaryState.name: cmAccPortQosShaperSecondaryState
cmAccPortQosShaperSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the QOS Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperCIRLo.name: cmAccPortQosShaperCIRLo
cmAccPortQosShaperCIRLo.description: This object represents the Commited Information Rate(CIR) (Lower 32 bits)of a Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperCIRHi.name: cmAccPortQosShaperCIRHi
cmAccPortQosShaperCIRHi.description: This object represents the Commited Information Rate(CIR) (Higher 32 bits) of a Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperEIRLo.name: cmAccPortQosShaperEIRLo
cmAccPortQosShaperEIRLo.description: This object represents the Excess Information Rate(EIR) (Higher 32 bits) on the Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperEIRHi.name: cmAccPortQosShaperEIRHi
cmAccPortQosShaperEIRHi.description: This object represents the Excess Information Rate(EIR) (Higher 32 bits) on the Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperCBS.name: cmAccPortQosShaperCBS
cmAccPortQosShaperCBS.description: This object represents the Commited Burst Size (CBS) of the Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperEBS.name: cmAccPortQosShaperEBS
cmAccPortQosShaperEBS.description: This object represents the Excess Burst Size (EBS) of the Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperBufferSize.name: cmAccPortQosShaperBufferSize
cmAccPortQosShaperBufferSize.description: This object represents the Buffer Size of the Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperCOS.name: cmAccPortQosShaperCOS
cmAccPortQosShaperCOS.description: This object provides the COS (Class of Service) value for the QOS Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperSoamCIRLo.name: cmAccPortQosShaperSoamCIRLo
cmAccPortQosShaperSoamCIRLo.description: This object represents the Soam Commited Information Rate(SOAM-CIR) (Lower 32 bits)of a Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperSoamCIRHi.name: cmAccPortQosShaperSoamCIRHi
cmAccPortQosShaperSoamCIRHi.description: This object represents the Soam Commited Information Rate(SOAM-CIR) (Higher 32 bits) of a Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperSoamEIRLo.description: This object represents the Soam Excess Information Rate(SOAM-EIR) (Higher 32 bits) on the Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperSoamEIRHi.name: cmAccPortQosShaperSoamEIRHi
cmAccPortQosShaperSoamEIRHi.description: This object represents the Soam Excess Information Rate(SOAM-EIR) (Higher 32 bits) on the Shaper.

cmAccPortQosShaperWredGreenMinQueueThres.description: This object represents the Wred green packet min queue threshold value.

cmAccPortQosShaperWredGreenDropProbabili.name: cmAccPortQosShaperWredGreenDropProbability
cmAccPortQosShaperWredGreenDropProbabili.description: This object represents the Wred green packet drop probability.

cmAccPortQosShaperWredYellowMinQueueThre.name: cmAccPortQosShaperWredYellowMinQueueThreshold
cmAccPortQosShaperWredYellowMinQueueThre.description: This object represents the Wred yellow packet min queue threshold value.

cmAccPortQosShaperWredYellowMaxQueueThre.name: cmAccPortQosShaperWredYellowMaxQueueThreshold
cmAccPortQosShaperWredYellowMaxQueueThre.description: This object represents the Wred yellow packet max queue threshold value.

cmAccPortQosShaperWredYellowDropProbabil.name: cmAccPortQosShaperWredYellowDropProbability
cmAccPortQosShaperWredYellowDropProbabil.description: This object represents the Wred yellow packet drop probability.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2CiscoGroupDispType.description: Deprecated - each Cisco protocol has its own disposition. Control Protocol Disposition for Cisco Group. This includes ISL, PAGP, UDLD, CDP, VTP, DTP, PSVTP+, UplinkFast, VLAN Bridge, L2PT. Note that a specific protocol filter overrides the group setting.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2IslDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2IslDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2IslDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for ISL (Inter Switch Link). MAC Address (01:00:0C:00:00:00).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PagpDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PagpDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PagpDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for PAGP (Port Aggregation Protocol). MAC Address (01:00:0C:CC:CC:CC), Ethertype(0x104).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2UdldDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2UdldDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2UdldDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for UDLD (Unidirectional Link Detection). MAC Address (01:00:0C:CC:CC:CC), Ethertype(0x111).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2CdpDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2CdpDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2CdpDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for CDP (Cisco Discovery Protocol). MAC Address (01:00:0C:CC:CC:CC), Ethertype(0x2000).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2VtpDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2VtpDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2VtpDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for VTP (VLAN Trunking Protocol). MAC Address (01:00:0C:CC:CC:CC), Ethertype(0x2003).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2DtpDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2DtpDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2DtpDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for DTP (Dynamic Trunking). MAC Address (01:00:0C:CC:CC:CC), Ethertype(0x2004).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PvstpPlusDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PvstpPlusDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PvstpPlusDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for Spanning Tree PVSTP+. MAC Address (01:00:0C:CC:CC:CC), Ethertype(0x10B).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2UplinkFastDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2UplinkFastDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2UplinkFastDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for STP UplinkFast. MAC Address (01:00:0C:CD:CD:CD), Ethertype(0x200A).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2VlanBridgeDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2VlanBridgeDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2VlanBridgeDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for VLAN Bridge. MAC Address (01:00:0C:CD:CD:CE), Ethertype(0x10C).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2L2PTDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2L2PTDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2L2PTDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for Layer 2 Protocol Tunnelling(L2PT). MAC Address (01:00:0C:CD:CD:D0).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2BridgeGroupDispTyp.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2BridgeGroupDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2BridgeGroupDispTyp.description: Deprecated - individual dispositions available for each MAC. Bridge Group Control Protocol Disposition Type. This includes BPDU, PAUSE (IEEE 802.3x Flow Control), LACP (Link Aggregation), LACP Marker (Marker), EFM OAM (IEEE 802.3 ah) and IEEE 802.1x Port Authentication, besides reserved MAC addresses from 01:80:C2:00:00:04 thru 01:80:C2:00:00:0F.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2BPDUDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2BPDUDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2BPDUDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for IEEE Spanning Tree(STP), MSTP (Multiple Spanning Tree) and RSTP (Rapid Reconfiguration of Spanning Tree). MAC Address (01:80:C2:00:00:00).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PauseDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PauseDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PauseDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for IEEE 802.3x Flow Control (PAUSE frames).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LACPDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LACPDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LACPDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for 802.3ad Link Aggregation Protocol. MAC Address (01:80:C2:00:00:03), Ethertype (0x8809), Subtype(01).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LACPMarkerDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LACPMarkerDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LACPMarkerDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for IEEE 802.3ad Marker Protocol. MAC Address (01:80:C2:00:00:03), Ethertype (0x8809), Subtype(02).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2EfmOamDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2EfmOamDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2EfmOamDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for IEEE 802.3ah EFM OAM. MAC Address (01:80:C2:00:00:03), Ethertype (0x8809), Subtype(03).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2SSMDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2SSMDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2SSMDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for Sync Status Messages. MAC Address (01:80:C2:00:00:02), Ethertype (0x19A7), Subtype(0A).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PortAuthenDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PortAuthenDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PortAuthenDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for IEEE 802.1x Protocol. MAC Address (01:80:C2:00:00:03), Ethertype (0x888E).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2BridgeReservedDisp.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2BridgeReservedDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2BridgeReservedDisp.description: Deprecated - individual dispositions available for each MAC. Control Protocol Disposition for Range of MAC Addresses from 01:80:C2:00:00:04 to 01:80:C2:00:00:0F.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LANBridgesDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LANBridgesDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LANBridgesDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for IEEE 802.1d LAN Bridge Managment. MAC Address (01:80:C2:00:00:10).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GARPGroupDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GARPGroupDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GARPGroupDispType.description: Deprecated - each GARP Group protocol has its own disposition. Group Disposition type which includes GMRP, GVRP and MAC Address from range 01:80:C2:00:00:20 to 01:80:C2:00:00:2F.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GMRPDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GMRPDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GMRPDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for GARP Multicast Registration Protocol. MAC Address (01:80:C2:00:00:20).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GVRPDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GVRPDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GVRPDispType.description: Control Protocol Disposition for GARP VLAN Registration Protocol. MAC Address (01:80:C2:00:00:21).

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GARPDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GARPDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2GARPDispType.description: Group Disposition type which includes GARP Reserved MAC Address from range 01:80:C2:00:00:22 to 01:80:C2:00:00:2F.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LLDPDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LLDPDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2LLDPDispType.description: Deprecated - each LLDP MAC protocol has its own disposition. LLDP (Link Layer Discovery Protocol) Disposition type. MAC Address 01:80:C2:00:00:0e, 01:80:C2:00:00:03, or 01:80:C2:00:00:00.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2ELMIDispType.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2ELMIDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2ELMIDispType.description: ELMI (Ethernet Local Management Interface) Disposition type. MAC Address 01:80:C2:00:00:07 and EtherType of 0x88EE.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2L2PTTunnelMac.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2L2PTTunnelMac
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2L2PTTunnelMac.description: Configurable Layer 2 Protocol Tunneling MAC Address. For protocols STP, CDP and VTP, with control protocol disposition as pass-thru-l2pt, this configured MAC address replaces the DA, upon encapsulation. For decapsulation, protocol signature and this configured MAC address are matched and the MAC address is replaced with the protocol's inferred MAC address.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2NearestLLDPDispTyp.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2NearestLLDPDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2NearestLLDPDispTyp.description: LLDP (Link Layer Discovery Protocol) Nearest Bridge Disposition type.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2NonTpmrLLDPDispTyp.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2NonTpmrLLDPDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2NonTpmrLLDPDispTyp.description: LLDP (Link Layer Discovery Protocol) Non-TPMR Bridge Disposition type.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2CustomerLLDPDispTy.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2CustomerLLDPDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2CustomerLLDPDispTy.description: LLDP (Link Layer Discovery Protocol) Customer Bridge Disposition type.

cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PtpUntaggedDispTyp.name: cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PtpUntaggedDispType
cmEthernetNetPortCpdV2PtpUntaggedDispTyp.description: PTP non forwarding untagged frame Disposition type.

bitsPortTable.name: bitsPortTable
bitsPortTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to BITS Port Facilities for configuration purposes.

bitsPortEntry.name: bitsPortEntry
bitsPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the bitsPortTable.

bitsPortTypeIndex.name: bitsPortTypeIndex
bitsPortTypeIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this BITS Port within the card. Value 1 stands for BITS-IN, 2 for BITS-OUT.

bitsPortIndex.name: bitsPortIndex
bitsPortIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this BITS Port within the card. Note that each BITs Port is uniquely identified by the indices neIndex, shelfIndex, slotIndex, bitsPortIndex.

bitsPortIfIndex.name: bitsPortIfIndex
bitsPortIfIndex.description: This object has the same value as ifIndex for Bits Port. An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Bits Port.

bitsPortEntityIndex.name: bitsPortEntityIndex
bitsPortEntityIndex.description: Entity Index from ENTITY-MIB for this port.

bitsPortAdminState.name: bitsPortAdminState
bitsPortAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the BITS Port.

bitsPortOperationalState.name: bitsPortOperationalState
bitsPortOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the BITS Port.

bitsPortSecondaryState.name: bitsPortSecondaryState
bitsPortSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the BITS Port.

bitsPortType.name: bitsPortType
bitsPortType.description: This object represents the BITS Port Type.

bitsPortLineType.name: bitsPortLineType
bitsPortLineType.description: This object represents the BITS Port Line Type. Determines whether the T1/E1 BITS port operates in T1, E1, or 2048kHz mode.

bitsPortLineCode.name: bitsPortLineCode
bitsPortLineCode.description: This object represents the BITS Port Line Code. When the port is configured for a Line Type of T1, the valid values are t1-b8zs and t1-ami and the default value is t1-b8zs. When the port is configured for a Line Type of E1, the valid values are e1-hdb3 and e1-ami and the default value is e1-hdb3. When the port is configured for a Line Type of 2048kHz, the value is none.

bitsPortFrameFormat.name: bitsPortFrameFormat
bitsPortFrameFormat.description: This object represents the BITS Port Frame Format. When the port is configured for a Line Type of T1, the valid values are t1-sf and t1-esf and the default value is t1-esf. When the port is configured for a Line Type of E1, the valid values are e1-unframed, e1-crc4, and e1-dualFrame and the default value is e1-crc4. When the port is configured for a Line Type of 2048kHz, the value is none. R4.1CC and R4.3CC do not support e1-unframed.

bitsPortSaBitDesignation.name: bitsPortSaBitDesignation
bitsPortSaBitDesignation.description: This object represents the BITS Port Sa Bit Designation. Determines which E1 Sa Bit is used to transmit/receive the SSM. For T1 and 2048khz Line Types, the only allowed value is None. For E1 Line Type, the default value is bit4 and it can only have a value of None if QL Mode is disabled, otherwise, None is an invalid value.

bitsPortQLModeEnabled.name: bitsPortQLModeEnabled
bitsPortQLModeEnabled.description: This object allows to specify whether the BITS Port can be enabled/disabled for QL Mode. When enabled, on receive side -port shall PEER the SSM (Sync Status Messages) slow protocol PDUs and take appropriate action When enabled, on transmit side -port shall periodically (once a second) transmit QL TLV information PDUs When disabled, on receive side, -port shall terminate and discard any SSM slow protocol PDUs When disabled, on transmit side -port shall not transmit any SSM slow protocol PDUs.

bitsPortExpectedQL.name: bitsPortExpectedQL
bitsPortExpectedQL.description: This object allows to specify the expected QL when the BITS Port is enabled for QL Mode. This object allows the user to set a minimum expected received Quality Level on the port. The default value shall be None.

bitsPortAssumedQL.name: bitsPortAssumedQL
bitsPortAssumedQL.description: This object allows to specify the assumed QL on the BITS Port. The Assumed QL is only meaningful if the Network Clock Type (see fsp150cm-sync.mib) is option1 and the port's QL Mode is disabled and the port is being used as an input reference source. Under these conditions, the specified QL value is assumed to be the Quality Level of the non-failed reference.

bitsPortReceivedQL.name: bitsPortReceivedQL
bitsPortReceivedQL.description: This object provides the Received QL value for the BITS port. If the BITS port's QL Mode is disabled, then the received QL value is not applicable.

bitsPortTransmitQL.name: bitsPortTransmitQL
bitsPortTransmitQL.description: This object provides the Transmitted QL value for the BITS port. If the BITS port's QL Mode is disabled, then the received QL value is not applicable.

bitsPortSquelchQL.name: bitsPortSquelchQL
bitsPortSquelchQL.description: This object allows to set the Squelch QL for the BITS-OUT port. The Squelch QL is only meaningful if the QL Mode is Enabled. The Squelch QL is used to determine whether or not to squelch the output of the BITS-OUT port. If the system's QL is lower than the Squelch QL, the output is squelched. If the BITS port's QL Mode is disabled, then the received QL value is not applicable.

bitsPortLineBuildOut.name: bitsPortLineBuildOut
bitsPortLineBuildOut.description: This object allows to manage the line build out on the BITS-OUT port when the Line Type is T1.

bitsPortImpedance.name: bitsPortImpedance
bitsPortImpedance.description: This object provides the impedance mode for the BITS-OUT port.

ieee1588EthernetPortTable.name: ieee1588EthernetPortTable
ieee1588EthernetPortTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to IEEE Ethernet Port Facilities for configuration purposes.

ieee1588EthernetPortEntry.name: ieee1588EthernetPortEntry
ieee1588EthernetPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the IEEE Ethernet Port Table.

ieee1588EthernetPortIndex.name: ieee1588EthernetPortIndex
ieee1588EthernetPortIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify the IEEE Ethernet Port.

ieee1588EthernetPortIfIndex.name: ieee1588EthernetPortIfIndex
ieee1588EthernetPortIfIndex.description: This object has the same value as ifIndex for the IEEE Ethernet Port.

ieee1588EthernetPortEntityIndex.name: ieee1588EthernetPortEntityIndex
ieee1588EthernetPortEntityIndex.description: Entity Index from ENTITY-MIB for this port.

ieee1588EthernetPortAdminState.name: ieee1588EthernetPortAdminState
ieee1588EthernetPortAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Port.

ieee1588EthernetPortOperationalState.name: ieee1588EthernetPortOperationalState
ieee1588EthernetPortOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Port.

ieee1588EthernetPortSecondaryState.name: ieee1588EthernetPortSecondaryState
ieee1588EthernetPortSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the Port.

ieee1588EthernetPortMTU.name: ieee1588EthernetPortMTU
ieee1588EthernetPortMTU.description: This object provides the MTU on the Port.

ieee1588EthernetPortMediaType.name: ieee1588EthernetPortMediaType
ieee1588EthernetPortMediaType.description: This object represents the type of Media.

ieee1588EthernetPortConfigSpeed.name: ieee1588EthernetPortConfigSpeed
ieee1588EthernetPortConfigSpeed.description: This object allows to configure the speed of the Port.

ieee1588EthernetPortNegotiatedSpeed.name: ieee1588EthernetPortNegotiatedSpeed
ieee1588EthernetPortNegotiatedSpeed.description: This object provides the negotiated speed of the Port.

ieee1588EthernetPortMDIXType.name: ieee1588EthernetPortMDIXType
ieee1588EthernetPortMDIXType.description: This object allows management of MDIX property on Port.

gps10MHzPortTable.name: gps10MHzPortTable
gps10MHzPortTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to GPS 10MHz Facilities for configuration purposes.

gps10MHzPortEntry.name: gps10MHzPortEntry
gps10MHzPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the GPS 10MHz Port Table.

gps10MHzPortIndex.name: gps10MHzPortIndex
gps10MHzPortIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify the IEEE Ethernet Port.

gps10MHzPortIfIndex.name: gps10MHzPortIfIndex
gps10MHzPortIfIndex.description: This object has the same value as ifIndex for the IEEE Ethernet Port.

gps10MHzPortEntityIndex.name: gps10MHzPortEntityIndex
gps10MHzPortEntityIndex.description: Entity Index from ENTITY-MIB for this port.

gps10MHzPortAdminState.name: gps10MHzPortAdminState
gps10MHzPortAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Port.

gps10MHzPortOperationalState.name: gps10MHzPortOperationalState
gps10MHzPortOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Port.

gps10MHzPortSecondaryState.name: gps10MHzPortSecondaryState
gps10MHzPortSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the Port.

gps10MHzPortSignalDirection.name: gps10MHzPortSignalDirection
gps10MHzPortSignalDirection.description: This object allows specification of the signal type (i.e. input or output).

gps10MHzPortSquelchControl.name: gps10MHzPortSquelchControl
gps10MHzPortSquelchControl.description: This object allows to set the Squelch Control for the 10MHz port. The Squelch Control is used to determine the type of squelch control used to squelch the output of the TOD port. Only option supported is squelch-ql.

gps10MHzPortSquelchQL.name: gps10MHzPortSquelchQL
gps10MHzPortSquelchQL.description: This object allows to set the Squelch QL for the 10MHz port. This value is used when f310MHzClockPortSquelchControl is squelch-ql. The Squelch QL is used to determine whether or not to squelch the output of the TOD port. If the system's QL is lower than the Squelch QL, the output is squelched.

gps10MHzPortFrequencySource.name: gps10MHzPortFrequencySource
gps10MHzPortFrequencySource.description: This object allows to set the Frequency Source for the Port.

gps10MHzPortClockClass.name: gps10MHzPortClockClass
gps10MHzPortClockClass.description: This object specify GPS port clock class.

gps10MHzPortClockAccuracy.name: gps10MHzPortClockAccuracy
gps10MHzPortClockAccuracy.description: This object specify GPS port clock accuracy.

gps10MHzPortTimeSource.name: gps10MHzPortTimeSource
gps10MHzPortTimeSource.description: This object specify GPS port time source.

gps10MHzPortAssumedQL.name: gps10MHzPortAssumedQL
gps10MHzPortAssumedQL.description: This object allows to specify the assumed QL on the GPS Port. The Assumed QL is only meaningful if the Network Clock Type (see fsp150cm-sync.mib) is option1 and the port's QL Mode is disabled and the port is being used as an input reference source. Under these conditions, the specified QL value is assumed to be the Quality Level of the non-failed reference.

gps10MHzPortAlias.name: gps10MHzPortAlias
gps10MHzPortAlias.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide an alias to the gps 10MHz Port entity.

cmEthernetNetPortClbTable.name: cmEthernetNetPortClbTable
cmEthernetNetPortClbTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Network Port Cable Length Benchmark.

cmEthernetNetPortClbEntry.name: cmEthernetNetPortClbEntry
cmEthernetNetPortClbEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetNetPortClbTable. These entries represent Cable Length Benchmarks on the Ethernet Network Port.

cmEthernetNetPortClbIndex.name: cmEthernetNetPortClbIndex
cmEthernetNetPortClbIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Cable Length Benchmark Entry specification.

cmEthernetNetPortClbEnabled.name: cmEthernetNetPortClbEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortClbEnabled.description: This enables specification of Cable Length Benchmark entry.

cmEthernetNetPortClbLength.name: cmEthernetNetPortClbLength
cmEthernetNetPortClbLength.description: Cable length of Cable Points Entry. The cable length is of the form XXX[.YY] where XX can be any integer value and YY allows precision of 2 decimals after the floating point. Note that .YY is optional.

cmEthernetNetPortClbDescr.name: cmEthernetNetPortClbDescr
cmEthernetNetPortClbDescr.description: A textual string containing description of cable span.

cmNetPortPrioMapTable.name: cmNetPortPrioMapTable
cmNetPortPrioMapTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Network Port Priority Mappings in multi Class of Service (COS) mode.

cmNetPortPrioMapEntry.name: cmNetPortPrioMapEntry
cmNetPortPrioMapEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmNetPortPrioMapTable.

cmNetPortPrioMapIndex.name: cmNetPortPrioMapIndex
cmNetPortPrioMapIndex.description: The integer index value corresponding to a priority value.

cmNetPortPrioMapInPriority.name: cmNetPortPrioMapInPriority
cmNetPortPrioMapInPriority.description: The integer index value corresponding to a priority value.

cmNetPortPrioMapCOS.name: cmNetPortPrioMapCOS
cmNetPortPrioMapCOS.description: This allows specification of the COS Priority, i.e. this helps in determining the appropriate COS Policer for the Flow.

cmNetPortPrioMapOuterTagPriority.name: cmNetPortPrioMapOuterTagPriority
cmNetPortPrioMapOuterTagPriority.description: This allows specification of the VLAN priority that will replace the outgoing (N2A direction) outer-tag's priority. Note that, each flow participates or not in outer-tag priority mapping, using the object 'cmFlowN2AOuterTagPrioEnabled'.

cmAccPortPcpDEEncTable.name: cmAccPortPcpDEEncTable
cmAccPortPcpDEEncTable.description: Ethernet Access Port PCP drop eligibility encoding table. This is applied to a frame that is egressing at the Access port.

cmAccPortPcpDEEncEntry.name: cmAccPortPcpDEEncEntry
cmAccPortPcpDEEncEntry.description: A conceptual row in the ethernetPBPcpDEEncPortTable.

cmAccPortPcpDEEncIndex.name: cmAccPortPcpDEEncIndex
cmAccPortPcpDEEncIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a row in the PCP drop eligible encoding table.

cmAccPortPcpDEEncInPriority.name: cmAccPortPcpDEEncInPriority
cmAccPortPcpDEEncInPriority.description: This object is the input priority that is translated to a drop eligibility priority or a drop ineligibility priority.

cmAccPortPcpDEEncDropIneligiblePrio.name: cmAccPortPcpDEEncDropIneligiblePrio
cmAccPortPcpDEEncDropIneligiblePrio.description: This object is the PCP value that has a priority value with implicit drop ineligibility encoded into it.

cmAccPortPcpDEEncDropEligiblePrio.name: cmAccPortPcpDEEncDropEligiblePrio
cmAccPortPcpDEEncDropEligiblePrio.description: This object is the PCP value that has a priority value with implicit drop eligibility encoded into it.

cmAccPortPcpDEDecTable.name: cmAccPortPcpDEDecTable
cmAccPortPcpDEDecTable.description: Ethernet Access Port PCP drop eligibility decoding table. This is applied to a frame that is ingressing at a port.

cmAccPortPcpDEDecEntry.name: cmAccPortPcpDEDecEntry
cmAccPortPcpDEDecEntry.description: A conceptual row in the ethernetPBPcpDEDecPortTable.

cmAccPortPcpDEDecIndex.name: cmAccPortPcpDEDecIndex
cmAccPortPcpDEDecIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a row in the PCP drop eligible decoding table.

cmAccPortPcpDEDecInPriority.name: cmAccPortPcpDEDecInPriority
cmAccPortPcpDEDecInPriority.description: This object is the input priority that is decoded to get priority and the drop eligibility of a frame.

cmAccPortPcpDEDecOutPriority.name: cmAccPortPcpDEDecOutPriority
cmAccPortPcpDEDecOutPriority.description: This object is the priority value decoded from a incoming PCP value.

cmAccPortPcpDEDecDropEligible.name: cmAccPortPcpDEDecDropEligible
cmAccPortPcpDEDecDropEligible.description: This object is the drop eligibility decoded from a incoming PCP value.
