cmAccPortPcpDEPairTable.name: cmAccPortPcpDEPairTable
cmAccPortPcpDEPairTable.description: Ethernet Access Port PCP drop eligibility priority pair table. The priority pair is encoded to same drop eligibility and drop ineligibility priority. Depending on the PCP DE Enc/Dec mode there can be upto 3 pairs in the table. There will one pair for 7P1D, two pairs for 6P2D and three pairs for 5P3D.

cmAccPortPcpDEPairEntry.name: cmAccPortPcpDEPairEntry
cmAccPortPcpDEPairEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmAccPortPcpDEPairEntry.

cmAccPortPcpDEPairIndex.name: cmAccPortPcpDEPairIndex
cmAccPortPcpDEPairIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a row in the PCP drop eligible priority pair table.

cmAccPortPcpDEDropIneligiblePrio.name: cmAccPortPcpDEDropIneligiblePrio
cmAccPortPcpDEDropIneligiblePrio.description: This object is the drop ineligible priority.

cmAccPortPcpDEDropEligiblePrio.name: cmAccPortPcpDEDropEligiblePrio
cmAccPortPcpDEDropEligiblePrio.description: This object is the drop eligible priority.

cmNetPortPcpDEEncTable.name: cmNetPortPcpDEEncTable
cmNetPortPcpDEEncTable.description: Ethernet Network Port PCP drop eligibility encoding table. This is applied to a frame that is egressing at the Network port.

cmNetPortPcpDEEncEntry.name: cmNetPortPcpDEEncEntry
cmNetPortPcpDEEncEntry.description: A conceptual row in the ethernetPBPcpDEEncPortTable.

cmNetPortPcpDEEncIndex.name: cmNetPortPcpDEEncIndex
cmNetPortPcpDEEncIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a row in the PCP drop eligible encoding table.

cmNetPortPcpDEEncInPriority.name: cmNetPortPcpDEEncInPriority
cmNetPortPcpDEEncInPriority.description: This object is the input priority that is translated to a drop eligibility priority or a drop ineligibility priority.

cmNetPortPcpDEEncDropIneligiblePrio.name: cmNetPortPcpDEEncDropIneligiblePrio
cmNetPortPcpDEEncDropIneligiblePrio.description: This object is the PCP value that has a priority value with implicit drop ineligibility encoded into it.

cmNetPortPcpDEEncDropEligiblePrio.name: cmNetPortPcpDEEncDropEligiblePrio
cmNetPortPcpDEEncDropEligiblePrio.description: This object is the PCP value that has a priority value with implicit drop eligibility encoded into it.

cmNetPortPcpDEDecTable.name: cmNetPortPcpDEDecTable
cmNetPortPcpDEDecTable.description: Ethernet Network Port PCP drop eligibility decoding table. This is applied to a frame that is ingressing at a port.

cmNetPortPcpDEDecEntry.name: cmNetPortPcpDEDecEntry
cmNetPortPcpDEDecEntry.description: A conceptual row in the ethernetPBPcpDEDecPortTable.

cmNetPortPcpDEDecIndex.name: cmNetPortPcpDEDecIndex
cmNetPortPcpDEDecIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a row in the PCP drop eligible decoding table.

cmNetPortPcpDEDecInPriority.name: cmNetPortPcpDEDecInPriority
cmNetPortPcpDEDecInPriority.description: This object is the input priority that is decoded to get priority and the drop eligibility of a frame.

cmNetPortPcpDEDecOutPriority.name: cmNetPortPcpDEDecOutPriority
cmNetPortPcpDEDecOutPriority.description: This object is the priority value decoded from a incoming PCP value.

cmNetPortPcpDEDecDropEligible.name: cmNetPortPcpDEDecDropEligible
cmNetPortPcpDEDecDropEligible.description: This object is the drop eligibility decoded from a incoming PCP value.

cmNetPortPcpDEPairTable.name: cmNetPortPcpDEPairTable
cmNetPortPcpDEPairTable.description: Ethernet Network Port PCP drop eligibility priority pair table. The priority pair is encoded to same drop eligibility and drop ineligibility priority. Depending on the PCP DE Enc/Dec mode there can be upto 3 pairs in the table. There will one pair for 7P1D, two pairs for 6P2D and three pairs for 5P3D.

cmNetPortPcpDEPairEntry.name: cmNetPortPcpDEPairEntry
cmNetPortPcpDEPairEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmNetPortPcpDEPairEntry.

cmNetPortPcpDEPairIndex.name: cmNetPortPcpDEPairIndex
cmNetPortPcpDEPairIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a row in the PCP drop eligible priority pair table.

cmNetPortPcpDEDropIneligiblePrio.name: cmNetPortPcpDEDropIneligiblePrio
cmNetPortPcpDEDropIneligiblePrio.description: This object is the drop ineligible priority.

cmNetPortPcpDEDropEligiblePrio.name: cmNetPortPcpDEDropEligiblePrio
cmNetPortPcpDEDropEligiblePrio.description: This object is the drop eligible priority.

cmEthernetTrafficPortTable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortTable
cmEthernetTrafficPortTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Facilities for configuration purposes.

cmEthernetTrafficPortEntry.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortEntry
cmEthernetTrafficPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetTrafficPortTable.

cmEthernetTrafficPortIndex.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortIndex
cmEthernetTrafficPortIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Ethernet Port within a card. Note that each Ethernet Port is uniquely identified by the indices neIndex, shelfIndex, slotIndex, cmEthernetTrafficPortIndex.

cmEthernetTrafficPortIfIndex.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortIfIndex
cmEthernetTrafficPortIfIndex.description: This object has the same value as ifIndex for Ethernet Port. An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortEntityIndex.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortEntityIndex
cmEthernetTrafficPortEntityIndex.description: Entity Index from ENTITY-MIB for this port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortAdminState.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortAdminState
cmEthernetTrafficPortAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOperationalState.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOperationalState
cmEthernetTrafficPortOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSecondaryState.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSecondaryState
cmEthernetTrafficPortSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortMTU.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortMTU
cmEthernetTrafficPortMTU.description: This object provides the MTU on the Ethernet Port. The object is made read-write for FSP150CC devices.

cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType
cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType.description: This object represents the type of Ethernet Media on the Ethernet Port. The media type includes, copper (1) fiber (2) coppersfp (3) CM Aggregation Product doesn't support copper.

cmEthernetTrafficPortConfigSpeed.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortConfigSpeed
cmEthernetTrafficPortConfigSpeed.description: This object allows to configure the speed of the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortNegotiatedSpeed.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortNegotiatedSpeed
cmEthernetTrafficPortNegotiatedSpeed.description: This object provides the negotiated speed of the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortMDIXType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortMDIXType
cmEthernetTrafficPortMDIXType.description: This object allows management of MDIX property on Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortMDIXStatus.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortMDIXStatus
cmEthernetTrafficPortMDIXStatus.description: This object provides the current MDIX status of the Ethernet port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpVendorName.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpVendorName
cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpVendorName.description: This object provides the vendor name of the SFP. This is applicable when cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpPartNumber.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpPartNumber
cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpPartNumber.description: This object provides the part number of the SFP. This is applicable when cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpSerialNumber.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpSerialNumber
cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpSerialNumber.description: This object provides the serial number of the SFP. This is shown only when cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType is fiber.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpDateOfManufactur.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpDateOfManufacture
cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpDateOfManufactur.description: This object provides the date of manufacture of the SFP. This is applicable when cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpConnectorValue.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpConnectorValue
cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpConnectorValue.description: This object provides the SFP connector value. This is applicable when cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLinkLength.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLinkLength
cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLinkLength.description: This object provides the SFP Link Length. This is applicable only when cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLaserWaveLength.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLaserWaveLength
cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLaserWaveLength.description: This object provides the SFP Laser Wave Length in nano meters. This is applicable only when cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType is fiber.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpMediaType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpMediaType
cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpMediaType.description: This object provides the SFP Media Type. This is applicable only when cmEthernetTrafficPortMediaType is fiber or coppersfp.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackConfig.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackConfig
cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackConfig.description: This object allows to initiate loopbacks on on the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackStatus.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackStatus
cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackStatus.description: This object provides status of the current loopback on the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackTime.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackTime
cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackTime.description: This object allows to specify time for timed-loopbacks on on the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackSwapSADA.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackSwapSADA
cmEthernetTrafficPortLoopbackSwapSADA.description: This object allows to specify whether or not the loopbacked frame will have the Source Address and Destination Address swapped.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopbackMa.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask
cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopbackMa.description: This object allows specification of the outer VLANs to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. Only 3 VLANs can be specified for vlan loopback. The various bit positions are: 1 Outer VLAN 1 Loopback Enabled 2 Outer VLAN 2 Loopback Enabled 4 Outer VLAN 3 Loopback Enabled

cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopback1.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopback1
cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopback1.description: This object allows specification of the outer VLAN 1 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopback2.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopback2
cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopback2.description: This object allows specification of the outer VLAN 2 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopback3.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopback3
cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopback3.description: This object allows specification of the outer VLAN 3 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetTrafficPortOuterVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdEnabled.description: This object allows enabling/disabling link loss forwarding on the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdSignalTy.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdSignalType
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdSignalTy.description: This object allows definition of the link loss forwarding signalling type. This is applicable only if cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdEnabled is enabled.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdTriggerT.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdTriggerTypes
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdTriggerT.description: This object allows definition of the link loss forwarding trigger types. This is applicable only if cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdEnabled is enabled.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdDelay.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdDelay
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdDelay.description: This object allows specification of the delay between detection of link loss and signalling of link loss forwarding. Time specified is in seconds.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdActive.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdActive
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdActive.description: This object provides the link loss forwarding status indicating if link loss forwarding is currently being signaled via the port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdPartnerE.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdPartnerEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdPartnerE.description: This object provides the indication of a link partners ability to support link loss forwarding via EFM, i.e. from received organization specific OAMPDUs.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdLocalLin.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdLocalLinkId
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdLocalLin.description: This object allows configuration of the Local Link Id on Ethernet port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdRemoteLi.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdRemoteLinkIds
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdRemoteLi.description: This object allows enabling/disabling Remote Link Ids on Ethernet port. the Ethernet port is able to distinguish the remote side client ports from the Remote Link Down PDUs coming from remote end. The cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdLocalLinkId must be set before set cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdRemoteLinkIds, By setting the Remote Link Ids seperated by the comma, e.g. 1,2,3,10,20..., up to 10 remote ID numbers can be added, number ranger is from 1 to 256(for EGX8.1, max value is 554). By setting nothing or '' to disable the Remote Link Ids.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdTxAction.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdTxActionType
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdTxAction.description: This object allows to specify the Ethernet Port's behavior when link loss forwarding trigger events occur on the Port. This provides ability to configure per Ethernet port LLF behavior.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdRxRLDLin.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdRxRLDLinkIds
cmEthernetTrafficPortLinkLossFwdRxRLDLin.description: This object provides the received Remote Link IDs in EFM RLD messages on the Ethernet Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamId.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamId
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamId.description: OAM Id. This is unique EFM OAM sublayer port id.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalVarRtrvsEna.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalVarRtrvsEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalVarRtrvsEna.description: This object allows specification of whether the Ethernet Port supports sending variable response OAMPDUs.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalLinkEventsE.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalLinkEventsEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalLinkEventsE.description: This object allows specification of whether the Ethernet Port supports interpreting Link Events.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalOamLoopback.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalOamLoopbacksSupported
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalOamLoopback.description: This object allows specification of whether the Ethernet Port is capable of OAM remote loopback mode.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalUnidirSuppo.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalUnidirSupportEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalUnidirSuppo.description: This object allows specification of whether the Ethernet Port is capable of sending OAMPDUs when the receive path is non-operational.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalMaxPDUSize.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalMaxPDUSize
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalMaxPDUSize.description: This object represents the largest OAMPDU, in octets, supported by the Ethernet Port. This value is compared to the remote Maximum PDU Size and the smaller of the two is used.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalMode.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalMode
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamLocalMode.description: This object allows to configure the OAM sublayer entity in either Active or Passive mode.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteMacAddress.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteMacAddress
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteMacAddress.description: This object allows retrieval of the Remote Mac Address.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteVarRtrvsEn.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteVarRtrvsEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteVarRtrvsEn.description: This object allows retrieval of whether the remote OAM entity supports sending variable response OAMPDUs.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteLinkEvents.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteLinkEventsEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteLinkEvents.description: This object allows retrieval of whether the remote OAM entity supports interpreting Link Events.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteOamLoopbac.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteOamLoopbacksSupported
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteOamLoopbac.description: This object allows retrieval of whether the remote OAM entity supports OAM remote loopback mode.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteUnidirSupp.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteUnidirSupportEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteUnidirSupp.description: This object allows retrieval of whether the remote OAM entity is capable of sending OAMPDUs when the receive path is non-operational.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteMaxPDUSize.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteMaxPDUSize
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteMaxPDUSize.description: This object allows retrieval of the remote OAM entity maximum OAMPDU size.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteMode.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteMode
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamRemoteMode.description: This object allows to retrieve whether the remote OAM sublayer entity is either in Active or Passive mode.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamEnabled.description: This object allows to manage the EFM OAM on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortOamAdminState.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortOamAdminState
cmEthernetTrafficPortOamAdminState.description: This object provides the EFM OAM Admin State.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSvcType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSvcType
cmEthernetTrafficPortSvcType.description: This object allows specification of whether the Ethernet Port is port based or vlan based.

cmEthernetTrafficPortRxPauseEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortRxPauseEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortRxPauseEnabled.description: This object defines the RxPause enable or disable of the port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortTxPauseEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortTxPauseEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortTxPauseEnabled.description: This object allows enabling/disabling transmit pause frames on Ethernet port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortAfpType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortAfpType
cmEthernetTrafficPortAfpType.description: This object allows specification of the Acceptable Frame Policy on Ethernet port. Users can specify whether the port supports only tagged frames, only untagged frames or both tagged and untagged frames.

cmEthernetTrafficPortShapingEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortShapingEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortShapingEnabled.description: This object allows to manage the Ethernet Port Shaping. When enabled, values in cmEthernetTrafficPortShapedSpeedLo and cmEthernetTrafficPortShapedSpeedHi are applicable.

cmEthernetTrafficPortShapedSpeedLo.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortShapedSpeedLo
cmEthernetTrafficPortShapedSpeedLo.description: This object allows to specify the lower 32 bits of the Ethernet Port Shaped speed. This value is applicable when cmEthernetTrafficPortShapingEnabled is enabled.

cmEthernetTrafficPortShapedSpeedHi.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortShapedSpeedHi
cmEthernetTrafficPortShapedSpeedHi.description: This object allows to specify the higher 32 bits of the Port Shaped speed. This value is applicable when cmEthernetTrafficPortShapingEnabled is enabled.

cmEthernetTrafficPortQinQEtherType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortQinQEtherType
cmEthernetTrafficPortQinQEtherType.description: This object allows to specify the Q-in-Q Ether Type on the Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortTagFrameControl.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortTagFrameControl
cmEthernetTrafficPortTagFrameControl.description: This object defines if c-tag/s-tag frame is allowed to pass through, available only when AFP is set to Tagged.

cmEthernetTrafficPortEgressVlanTrunkingE.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortEgressVlanTrunkingEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortEgressVlanTrunkingE.description: This object allows to enable or disable the VLAN trunking on Ethernet port. Disabling VLAN trunking removes all VLAN tags before transmitting traffic out of the port. This object is only applicable for connection-oriented, evpl service type.

cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPushPVIDEnab.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPushPVIDEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPushPVIDEnab.description: This object allows to specify whether cmEthernetTrafficPortPortVlanId value will be PUSHed on untagged frames or not in the ingress direction. This object is only applicable for connection-oriented, evpl service type.

cmEthernetTrafficPortEgressPopPVIDEnable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortEgressPopPVIDEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortEgressPopPVIDEnable.description: This object allows to specify whether cmEthernetTrafficPortPortVlanId value will be POPed in the egress direction. This object is only applicable for connection-oriented, evpl service type.

cmEthernetTrafficPortEgressPopPriorityVi.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortEgressPopPriorityVidEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortEgressPopPriorityVi.description: This object defines the egress PopPriorityVid enable or disable of the port. If it is enabled, the outgoing packets with VID=Priority VLAN ID will be swapped back to VID=0.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPortVlanId.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPortVlanId
cmEthernetTrafficPortPortVlanId.description: This object allows to specify the Ethernet Port VLAN Id to PUSH on untagged frames in the to Network direction. This object is only applicable for connection-oriented, evpl service type, when cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPushPVIDEnabled is set to true.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPortVlanPriority.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPortVlanPriority
cmEthernetTrafficPortPortVlanPriority.description: This object allows to specify the Ethernet Port VLAN Priority for the PUSHed VLAN tag (specified by cmEthernetTrafficPortPortVlanId) on untagged frames in the ingress direction. This object is only applicable for connection-oriented, evpl service type, when cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPushPVIDEnabled is set to true.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPriorityVlanId.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPriorityVlanId
cmEthernetTrafficPortPriorityVlanId.description: This object allows to specify the Ethernet Priority VLAN Id to replace the null-tagged or priority tagged frames in the to ingress direction. This object is only applicable for connection-oriented, evpl service type.

cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPrioMapMode.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPrioMapMode
cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPrioMapMode.description: This object allows to specify the Ethernet Port Priority Mapping Mode used for classification of frames. This object is only applicable for connection-oriented, evpl service type.

cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressCOSPriority.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressCOSPriority
cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressCOSPriority.description: This object is used to specify whether the EthernetTrafficPort uses the inner-tag or the outer-tag in determining the COS (Class of Service).

cmEthernetTrafficPortSyncEEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSyncEEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortSyncEEnabled.description: This object allows to specify whether the Ethernet Port can be enabled/disabled for Synchronous Ethernet. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports. When enabled, on receive side -port can extract the frequency of its input signal and pass the recovered clock to the system clock -port processes the ESMC(Ethernet Synchronization Messaging Channel) and extracts the QL (when also QL enabled) -port is eligible to be selected as a system clock reference When enabled, on transmit side -port's transmit clock is locked to the system clock -port generates an ESMC to generate a QL (when also QL enabled) When disabled, on receive side, -port does not pass the recovered clock to the system clock -port does not process the ESMC (if present) -port is not eligible to be selected as a system clock reference When disabled, on transmit side -port's output frequency may be synchronized to the system clock -port does not generate an ESMC.

cmEthernetTrafficPortQLModeEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortQLModeEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortQLModeEnabled.description: This object allows to specify whether the Ethernet Port can be enabled/disabled for QL Mode. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports, when cmEthernetTrafficPortQLModeEnabled is set to true. When enabled, on receive side -port shall PEER the SSM (Sync Status Messages) slow protocol PDUs and take appropriate action When enabled, on transmit side -port shall periodically (once a second) transmit QL TLV information PDUs When disabled, on receive side, -port shall terminate and discard any SSM slow protocol PDUs When disabled, on transmit side -port shall not transmit any SSM slow protocol PDUs.

cmEthernetTrafficPortExpectedQL.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortExpectedQL
cmEthernetTrafficPortExpectedQL.description: This object allows to specify the expected QL when the Ethernet Port is enabled for QL Mode. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports, when cmEthernetTrafficPortQLModeEnabled is set to true. This object allows the user to set a minimum expected received Quality Level on the port. The valid values depend upon the SYNC entity Network Clock Type. A value of None represents that a minimum Quality Level is not expected. The default value shall be None.

cmEthernetTrafficPortAssumedQL.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortAssumedQL
cmEthernetTrafficPortAssumedQL.description: This object allows to specify the assumed QL on the Ethernet Port. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports. The Assumed QL is only meaningful if the Network Clock Type (see fsp150cm-sync.mib) is option1 and the port TransmitQL Mode is disabled and the port is being used as an input reference source. Under these conditions, the specified QL value is assumed to be the Quality Level of the non-failed reference.

cmEthernetTrafficPortReceivedQL.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortReceivedQL
cmEthernetTrafficPortReceivedQL.description: This object provides the Received QL value for the Ethernet port. If the Ethernet port TransmitQL Mode is disabled, then the received QL value is not applicable.This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports.

cmEthernetTrafficPortTransmitQL.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortTransmitQL
cmEthernetTrafficPortTransmitQL.description: This object provides the Transmitted QL value for the Ethernet port. If the Ethernet port TransmitQL Mode is disabled, then the received QL value is not applicable. This object is only applicable for Synchronous Ethernet capable ports.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPhyType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPhyType
cmEthernetTrafficPortPhyType.description: This object is valid only to XGE card. And the value should be LAN or WAN when it is XGE card.

cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLaserWaveLengthP.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLaserWaveLengthPicometer
cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLaserWaveLengthP.description: This object provide laser wavelength pico value. For example, laser wavelength is 1510.01, then cmEthernetTrafficPortSfpLaserWaveLength=1510 and cmTrafficPortSfpLaserWaveLengthPicometer=10.

cmEthernetTrafficPortRowStatus.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortRowStatus
cmEthernetTrafficPortRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cmEthernetTrafficPortRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with neRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cmEthernetTrafficPortRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

cmEthernetTrafficPortSSMRemoteMacAddress.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortSSMRemoteMacAddress
cmEthernetTrafficPortSSMRemoteMacAddress.description: This object allows retrieval of the Remote Mac Address, when the port is peering using SSM.

cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopbackMa.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask
cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopbackMa.description: This object allows specification of the inner VLANs to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. Only 3 VLANs can be specified for vlan loopback. The various bit positions are: 1 Inner VLAN 1 Loopback Enabled 2 Inner VLAN 2 Loopback Enabled 4 Inner VLAN 3 Loopback Enabled

cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopback1.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopback1
cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopback1.description: This object allows specification of the inner VLAN 1 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopback2.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopback2
cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopback2.description: This object allows specification of the inner VLAN 2 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopback3.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopback3
cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopback3.description: This object allows specification of the inner VLAN 3 to be looped back when port is in vlan(terminal/facility) loopback configuration. This is valid only if the corresponding bit in cmEthernetTrafficPortInnerVlanLoopbackMask is set. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLaserWDMChannel.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLaserWDMChannel
cmEthernetTrafficPortLaserWDMChannel.description: Channel number of WDM tunable XFP setting.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLaserIsTunable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLaserIsTunable
cmEthernetTrafficPortLaserIsTunable.description: This object means this module whether tunnable.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLaserFrequency.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLaserFrequency
cmEthernetTrafficPortLaserFrequency.description: This object describes this module's frequency, and the step is 1GHZ.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDeiEnable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDeiEnable
cmEthernetTrafficPortDeiEnable.description: This object describes whether use DEI bit in S-tag to recognize Drop Eligibility Parameter for ingress S-tag packets or Set DEI bit for egress S-tag Packets. This object is still supported by OSA8.1.1

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncType
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncType.description: This object describes the PCP encoding mode for egress packets and the PCP decoding mode for ingress packets on this port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairsAction.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairsAction
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairsAction.description: This object describes this port pcp de pairs action.

cmEthernetTrafficPortInitiateDiag.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortInitiateDiag
cmEthernetTrafficPortInitiateDiag.description: This object allows to initiate Etherjack diagnosis on the Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair1Cond.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair1Cond
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair1Cond.description: This object provides diagnosis results for the cable Pair 1 on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair2Cond.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair2Cond
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair2Cond.description: This object provides diagnosis results for the cable Pair 2 on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair3Cond.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair3Cond
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair3Cond.description: This object provides diagnosis results for the cable Pair 3 on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair4Cond.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair4Cond
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnosePair4Cond.description: This object provides diagnosis results for the cable Pair 4 on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseAutoNegCond.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseAutoNegCond
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseAutoNegCond.description: This object provides auto negotiation results of the diagnosis test on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseLpbkCond.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseLpbkCond
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseLpbkCond.description: This object provides port loopback results of the diagnosis test on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseEfmLpbkCond.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseEfmLpbkCond
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseEfmLpbkCond.description: This object provides remote EFM loopback results of the diagnosis test on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseResult.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseResult
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseResult.description: This object provides results of the diagnosis test in string form on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseTestStatus.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseTestStatus
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseTestStatus.description: This object provides the current status of the diagnosis test on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseTestTime.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseTestTime
cmEthernetTrafficPortDiagnoseTestTime.description: This object provides the time when diagnosis test was last executed.

cmEthernetTrafficPortAutoDiagEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortAutoDiagEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortAutoDiagEnabled.description: This object allows to enable or disable the automatic Cable Diagnostic tests when the cable is removed from the port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortDeleteEntitiesActio.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortDeleteEntitiesAction
cmEthernetTrafficPortDeleteEntitiesActio.description: This object allows to delete esa entities relate this port and Cfm entities relate this port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortMaxMpFpNum.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortMaxMpFpNum
cmEthernetTrafficPortMaxMpFpNum.description: This object allows to set the mpflow max fp number, and now only the ports on ethernet10x1GCard, ethernet1x10GCard, ethernet1x10GHighPerCard, ethernet10x1GHighPerCard support this attribute. for others, cann't be set and will return 0.

cmEthernetTrafficPortJdsuLoopbackEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortJdsuLoopbackEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortJdsuLoopbackEnabled.description: This object allows to enable or disable jdsu loopback on this port. Note: This object is deprecated.

cmEthernetTrafficPortJdsuLoopbackVlanId.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortJdsuLoopbackVlanId
cmEthernetTrafficPortJdsuLoopbackVlanId.description: This object allows to set the jdsu loopback vlan. if status is jdsu-terminal-port-tailend(19) or jdsu-facility-port-tailend(21), then VID is 0 means not applicable. Note: This object is deprecated.

cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPopPriorityV.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPopPriorityVidEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPopPriorityV.description: This object defines the Ingress PopPriorityVid enable or disable of the port. If it is enabled, then incoming priority tagged packet's VID is swapped to Priority VLAN ID.

cmEthernetTrafficPortRxDeiAction.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortRxDeiAction
cmEthernetTrafficPortRxDeiAction.description: This object allows to specify the Receive DEI Action.

cmEthernetTrafficPortTxDeiAction.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortTxDeiAction
cmEthernetTrafficPortTxDeiAction.description: This object allows to specify the Transmit DEI Action.

cmEthernetTrafficPortRxDeiOuterTagType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortRxDeiOuterTagType
cmEthernetTrafficPortRxDeiOuterTagType.description: This object allows to specify the Receive DEI Outer Tag Type.

cmEthernetTrafficPortTxDeiOuterTagType.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortTxDeiOuterTagType
cmEthernetTrafficPortTxDeiOuterTagType.description: This object allows to specify the Transmit DEI Outer Tag Type.

cmElineFlowTable.name: cmElineFlowTable
cmElineFlowTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Flows for configuration purposes.

cmElineFlowEntry.name: cmElineFlowEntry
cmElineFlowEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmElineFlowTable. These entries represent an Flow.

cmElineFlowIndex.name: cmElineFlowIndex
cmElineFlowIndex.description: The integer index value corresponding to an Flow.

cmElineFlowCircuitName.name: cmElineFlowCircuitName
cmElineFlowCircuitName.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide a circuit identifier with the Flow.

cmElineFlowAdminState.name: cmElineFlowAdminState
cmElineFlowAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Flow.

cmElineFlowOperationalState.name: cmElineFlowOperationalState
cmElineFlowOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Flow.

cmElineFlowSecondaryState.name: cmElineFlowSecondaryState
cmElineFlowSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the Flow.

cmElineFlowFP1.name: cmElineFlowFP1
cmElineFlowFP1.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide a flowpoint with the Flow.

cmElineFlowFP2.name: cmElineFlowFP2
cmElineFlowFP2.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide another flowpoint with the Flow.

cmElineFlowStorageType.name: cmElineFlowStorageType
cmElineFlowStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmElineFlowRowStatus.name: cmElineFlowRowStatus
cmElineFlowRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cmElineFlowRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with cmElineFlowRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cmElineFlowRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

cmFlowPointTable.name: cmFlowPointTable
cmFlowPointTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to FlowPoint for configuration purposes.

cmFlowPointEntry.name: cmFlowPointEntry
cmFlowPointEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmFlowPointTable. These entries represent an FlowPoint. If the flowpoint attached to a lag, the slotIndex should be 255(255 is used to identify the flowpoint belongs to lag), and the cmEthernetTrafficPortIndex should be the f3LagIndex.

cmFlowPointIndex.name: cmFlowPointIndex
cmFlowPointIndex.description: The integer index value corresponding to an FlowPoint.

cmFlowPointCircuitName.name: cmFlowPointCircuitName
cmFlowPointCircuitName.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide a circuit identifier with the FlowPoint.

cmFlowPointAdminState.name: cmFlowPointAdminState
cmFlowPointAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the FlowPoint.

cmFlowPointOperationalState.name: cmFlowPointOperationalState
cmFlowPointOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the FlowPoint.

cmFlowPointSecondaryState.name: cmFlowPointSecondaryState
cmFlowPointSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the FlowPoint.

cmFlowPointAssociatedFlowId.name: cmFlowPointAssociatedFlowId
cmFlowPointAssociatedFlowId.description: This object provides the association of an Flow with an FlowPoint.

cmFlowPointIngressMultiCOS.name: cmFlowPointIngressMultiCOS
cmFlowPointIngressMultiCOS.description: This object allows specification of ingress multiple COS (Class of Service) FlowPoint.

cmFlowPointIngressCOS.name: cmFlowPointIngressCOS
cmFlowPointIngressCOS.description: This object allows specification of ingress COS (Class of Service) FlowPoint.

cmFlowPointIngressVlanMemberList.name: cmFlowPointIngressVlanMemberList
cmFlowPointIngressVlanMemberList.description: It allows specification of VLAN members of the FlowPoint. VLAN members are comma separated, of the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. VLAN members can be of the form X-* or X (vlan X with all priorities), *-Y (all vlans with priority Y), and X1:X2 (range of vlans from X1 to X2, all priorities). Members with specific VLAN Id and specific VLAN Priority are not supported. Once the flowpoint is created, this attribute can only be updated using cmFlowPointVlanMemberAction and cmFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan objects.

cmFlowPointVlanMemberAction.name: cmFlowPointVlanMemberAction
cmFlowPointVlanMemberAction.description: This object allows to add or remove the VLAN members specified by cmFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan object. SNMP manager must first configure the VLAN member to be added/removed in the object cmFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan and then should specify cmFlowPointVlanMemberAction on whether to add/remove the specified VLAN member.

cmFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan.name: cmFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan
cmFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan.description: This object allows adding/removing VLAN members to a flowpoint. VLAN member is of the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. VLAN members can be of the form X-* (vlan X with all priorities), *-Y (all vlans with priority Y), and X1:X2 (range of vlans from X1 to X2, all priorities). Members with specific VLAN Id and specific VLAN Priority are not supported. In order to add/remove VLAN member to a flow, user must specify this object with appropriate VLAN and then invoke cmFlowPointVlanMemberAction.

cmFlowPointIngressUntaggedFrameEnabled.name: cmFlowPointIngressUntaggedFrameEnabled
cmFlowPointIngressUntaggedFrameEnabled.description: This object allows to specify whether or not the flowpoint supports untagged frame.

cmFlowPointCTagControl.name: cmFlowPointCTagControl
cmFlowPointCTagControl.description: This object allows specification of the tag management operation on the C-TAG. Supported types are 'push', 'pushvid', 'swaptag', 'swapvid' and 'none'. If the type is 'push', the VLAN Id (cmFlowPointCTagVlanId) and priority (cmFlowPointCTagVlanPriority) are pushed onto the frame; if the type is 'pushvid', only the VLAN Id (12 bits) is pushed, the Priority is copied from incoming tag's priority; if the type is 'swaptag', both VLAN Id and Priority (15 bits) are swapped with the specified cmFlowPointCTagVlanId and cmFlowPointCTagVlanPriority; if the type is 'swapvid', only the VLAN Id (12 bits) are swapped with the specified cmFlowPointCTagVlanId; if the type is 'none', no C-TAG management is performed.

cmFlowPointCTagVlanId.name: cmFlowPointCTagVlanId
cmFlowPointCTagVlanId.description: This object allows specification of the VLAN Id to be pushed or swapped, based on the value of cmFlowPointIngressCTagControl. It is applicable for 'push', 'swaptag', 'swapvid' and 'pushvid' control types.

cmFlowPointCTagVlanPriority.name: cmFlowPointCTagVlanPriority
cmFlowPointCTagVlanPriority.description: This object allows specification of the VLAN Priority to be pushed or swapped, based on the value of cmFlowPointIngressCTagControl. It is applicable for 'push' and 'swaptag' control types.

cmFlowPointSTagControl.name: cmFlowPointSTagControl
cmFlowPointSTagControl.description: This object allows specification of the tag management operation on the S-TAG. Supported types are 'push', 'pushvid', 'swaptag', 'swapvid' and 'none'. If the type is 'push', the VLAN Id (cmFlowPointSTagVlanId) and priority (cmFlowPointSTagVlanPriority) are pushed onto the frame; if the type is 'pushvid', only the VLAN Id (12 bits) is pushed, the Priority is copied from incoming tag's priority; if the type is 'swaptag', both VLAN Id and Priority (15 bits) are swapped with the specified cmFlowPointSTagVlanId and cmFlowPointSTagVlanPriority; if the type is 'swapvid', only the VLAN Id (12 bits) are swapped with the specified cmFlowPointSTagVlanId; if the type is 'none', no S-TAG management is performed.

cmFlowPointSTagVlanId.name: cmFlowPointSTagVlanId
cmFlowPointSTagVlanId.description: This object allows specification of the VLAN Id to be pushed or swapped, based on the value of cmFlowPointIngressSTagControl. It is applicable for 'push', 'swaptag', 'swapvid' and 'pushvid' control types.

cmFlowPointSTagVlanPriority.name: cmFlowPointSTagVlanPriority
cmFlowPointSTagVlanPriority.description: This object allows specification of the VLAN Priority to be pushed or swapped, based on the value of cmFlowPointIngressSTagControl. It is applicable for 'push' and 'swaptag' control types.

cmFlowPointEgressOuterTagPrioMapEnabled.name: cmFlowPointEgressOuterTagPrioMapEnabled
cmFlowPointEgressOuterTagPrioMapEnabled.description: This object defines whether to use the Egress Prio Mapping to swap the priority of outer tag. When Enabled,it indicates that the operation specified in the EgressPrioMapTable would be applied to Flow for specified COS. When Disabled,the EgressPrioMapTable operations are ignored for specified Flow COS.

cmFlowPointColorMarkingSupported.name: cmFlowPointColorMarkingSupported
cmFlowPointColorMarkingSupported.description: This object defines the egress color marking. If set to Enabled, the DEI bit of S-tag pushed will be remarked according the meter result. If set to Disabled, the DEI bit is forced to 0.

cmFlowPointAssociatedAclProfile.name: cmFlowPointAssociatedAclProfile
cmFlowPointAssociatedAclProfile.description: This object provides the association of an Flow with an ACL profile.

cmFlowPointSESFramesLossThresholdRatio.name: cmFlowPointSESFramesLossThresholdRatio
cmFlowPointSESFramesLossThresholdRatio.description: This object is used to specify the frame-loss ratio per flow that starts counting Severely Errored Seconds (SES) on the flowpoint. This functionality is applicable if the flowpoint is monitored using the Y.1731 ESA functionality.

cmFlowPointStorageType.name: cmFlowPointStorageType
cmFlowPointStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmFlowPointRowStatus.name: cmFlowPointRowStatus
cmFlowPointRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cmFlowPointRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with cmFlowPointRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cmFlowPointRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

cmFlowPointDefaultMemberEnabled.name: cmFlowPointDefaultMemberEnabled
cmFlowPointDefaultMemberEnabled.description: defaultMemberEnabled with enabled means that on this FP, the membership is all the tag packets without match any other membership associated to the port. Untagged means untagged flow. Default only care tagged flow.

cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitEnabled.name: cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitEnabled
cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitEnabled.description: Whether multicast packets need be limited per FP.

cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitSpeedLo.name: cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitSpeedLo
cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitSpeedLo.description: The rate limiting for multicast packets per FP When cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitEnabled and the value is 0, it means all multicast frame are dropped. This objects only represents low 32 bits.

cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitSpeedHi.name: cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitSpeedHi
cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitSpeedHi.description: The rate limiting for multicast packets per FP When cmFlowPointMcastRateLimitEnabled and the value is 0, it means all multicast frame are dropped. This objects only represents high 32 bits.

cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitEnabled.name: cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitEnabled
cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitEnabled.description: Whether broadcast packets need be limited per FP.

cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitSpeedLo.name: cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitSpeedLo
cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitSpeedLo.description: The rate limiting for broadcast packets per FP When cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitEnabled and the value is 0, it means all multicast frame are dropped. This objects only represents low 32 bits.

cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitSpeedHi.name: cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitSpeedHi
cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitSpeedHi.description: The rate limiting for broadcast packets per FP When cmFlowPointBcastRateLimitEnabled and the value is 0, it means all multicast frame are dropped. This objects only represents high 32 bits.

cmFlowPointSplitHorizonGroupOID.name: cmFlowPointSplitHorizonGroupOID
cmFlowPointSplitHorizonGroupOID.description: Specifies the Split-Horizon Group EID. If there is no SHG, the value is none.

cmFlowPointLoopAvoidance.name: cmFlowPointLoopAvoidance
cmFlowPointLoopAvoidance.description: EID of this associated Loop Avoidance protocol entity. A value of NONE indicates there is no loop avoidance protocol. Currently ERP EID is filled when ELAN service is created.

cmFlowPointHierarchicalCosEnabled.name: cmFlowPointHierarchicalCosEnabled
cmFlowPointHierarchicalCosEnabled.description: Enable or Disable Hierarchical COS shaping (flow shaping).

cmFlowPointWfqQid.name: cmFlowPointWfqQid
cmFlowPointWfqQid.description: This attribute description the WFQ Qid.

cmFlowPointWfqOutPriority.name: cmFlowPointWfqOutPriority
cmFlowPointWfqOutPriority.description: This attribute description the WFQ out priority.

cmFlowPointMaximumBWLo.name: cmFlowPointMaximumBWLo
cmFlowPointMaximumBWLo.description: This attribute description the flow point maximum bandwidth. This objects only represents low 32 bits.

cmFlowPointMaximumBWHi.name: cmFlowPointMaximumBWHi
cmFlowPointMaximumBWHi.description: This attribute description the flow point maximum bandwidth. This objects only represents high 32 bits.

cmFlowPointGuaranteedBWLo.name: cmFlowPointGuaranteedBWLo
cmFlowPointGuaranteedBWLo.description: This attribute description the flow point guaranteed bandwidth. This objects only represents low 32 bits.

cmFlowPointGuaranteedBWHi.name: cmFlowPointGuaranteedBWHi
cmFlowPointGuaranteedBWHi.description: This attribute description the flow point guaranteed bandwidth. This objects only represents high 32 bits.

cmFlowPointRefPrioMapProfile.name: cmFlowPointRefPrioMapProfile
cmFlowPointRefPrioMapProfile.description: This object allows to set priority map profile.

cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitEnabled.name: cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitEnabled
cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitEnabled.description: Whether multicast packets and broadcast packets need be limited per FP.

cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitSpeedLo.name: cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitSpeedLo
cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitSpeedLo.description: The rate limiting for multicast packets and broadcast packets per FP When cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitEnabled and the value is 0, it means all multicast frame are dropped. This objects only represents low 32 bits.

cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitSpeedHi.name: cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitSpeedHi
cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitSpeedHi.description: The rate limiting for multicast packets and broadcast packets per FP When cmFlowPointMcastAndBcastRateLimitEnabled and the value is 0, it means all multicast frame are dropped. This objects only represents high 32 bits.

cmOAMFlowPointTable.name: cmOAMFlowPointTable
cmOAMFlowPointTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to OAMFlowPoint for configuration purposes.

cmOAMFlowPointEntry.name: cmOAMFlowPointEntry
cmOAMFlowPointEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmOAMFlowPointTable. These entries represent an FlowPoint. If the oam flowpoint attached to a lag, the slotIndex should be 255(255 is used to identify the oam flowpoint belongs to lag), and the cmEthernetTrafficPortIndex should be the f3LagIndex.

cmOAMFlowPointIndex.name: cmOAMFlowPointIndex
cmOAMFlowPointIndex.description: The integer index value corresponding to an OAMFlowPoint.

cmOAMFlowPointCircuitName.name: cmOAMFlowPointCircuitName
cmOAMFlowPointCircuitName.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide a circuit identifier with the OAMFlowPoint.

cmOAMFlowPointAdminState.name: cmOAMFlowPointAdminState
cmOAMFlowPointAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the OAMFlowPoint.

cmOAMFlowPointOperationalState.name: cmOAMFlowPointOperationalState
cmOAMFlowPointOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the OAMFlowPoint.

cmOAMFlowPointSecondaryState.name: cmOAMFlowPointSecondaryState
cmOAMFlowPointSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the OAMFlowPoint.

cmOAMFlowPointIngressVlanMemberList.name: cmOAMFlowPointIngressVlanMemberList
cmOAMFlowPointIngressVlanMemberList.description: It allows specification of VLAN members of the OAMFlowPoint. VLAN members are comma separated, of the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. VLAN members can be of the form X-* or X (vlan X with all priorities), *-Y (all vlans with priority Y), and X1:X2 (range of vlans from X1 to X2, all priorities). Members with specific VLAN Id and specific VLAN Priority are not supported. Once the flowpoint is created, this attribute can only be updated using cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberAction and cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan objects.

cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberAction.name: cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberAction
cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberAction.description: This object allows to add or remove the VLAN members specified by cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan object. SNMP manager must first configure the VLAN member to be added/removed in the object cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan and then should specify cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberAction on whether to add/remove the specified VLAN member.

cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan.name: cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan
cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberActionVlan.description: This object allows adding/removing VLAN members to a oam flowpoint. VLAN member is of the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. VLAN members can be of the form X-* (vlan X with all priorities), *-Y (all vlans with priority Y), and X1:X2 (range of vlans from X1 to X2, all priorities). Members with specific VLAN Id and specific VLAN Priority are not supported. In order to add/remove VLAN member to a flow, user must specify this object with appropriate VLAN and then invoke cmOAMFlowPointVlanMemberAction.

cmOAMFlowPointIngressUntaggedFrameSuppor.name: cmOAMFlowPointIngressUntaggedFrameSupported
cmOAMFlowPointIngressUntaggedFrameSuppor.description: This object allows to specify whether or not the OAMFlowPoint supports untagged frame.

cmOAMFlowPointSESFramesLossThresholdRati.name: cmOAMFlowPointSESFramesLossThresholdRatio
cmOAMFlowPointSESFramesLossThresholdRati.description: This object is used to specify the frame-loss ratio per flow that starts counting Severely Errored Seconds (SES) on the oam flowpoint. This functionality is applicable if the oam flowpoint is monitored using the Y.1731 ESA functionality.

cmOAMFlowPointStorageType.name: cmOAMFlowPointStorageType
cmOAMFlowPointStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmOAMFlowPointRowStatus.name: cmOAMFlowPointRowStatus
cmOAMFlowPointRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cmOAMFlowPointRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with cmOAMFlowPointRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cmOAMFlowPointRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

cmIngressPrioMapTable.name: cmIngressPrioMapTable
cmIngressPrioMapTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ingress Priority Mapping for configuration purposes.

cmIngressPrioMapEntry.name: cmIngressPrioMapEntry
cmIngressPrioMapEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmIngressPrioMapTable.

cmIngressPrioMapIndex.name: cmIngressPrioMapIndex
cmIngressPrioMapIndex.description: The integer index value corresponding to a priority value based on the cmEthernetTrafficPortPrioMapMode. In case of TOS and 8021P, valid indices are 1 to 8, in case of DSCP, valid indices are 1 to 64.

cmIngressPrioMapInPriority.name: cmIngressPrioMapInPriority
cmIngressPrioMapInPriority.description: The integer index value corresponding to a priority value based on the cmEthernetTrafficPortIngressPrioMapMode. In case of TOS and 8021P, valid indices are 0 to 7, in case of DSCP, valid indices are 0 to 63.

cmIngressPrioMapCOS.name: cmIngressPrioMapCOS
cmIngressPrioMapCOS.description: This allows specification of the COS Priority, i.e. this helps in determining the appropriate COS Policer for the Flow.

cmEgressPrioMapTable.name: cmEgressPrioMapTable
cmEgressPrioMapTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Egress Priority Mapping for configuration purposes.

cmEgressPrioMapEntry.name: cmEgressPrioMapEntry
cmEgressPrioMapEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEgressPrioMapTable.

cmEgressCOSIndex.name: cmEgressCOSIndex
cmEgressCOSIndex.description: The integer index used to uniquely identify this Egress Priority Map Entry

cmEgressCOS.name: cmEgressCOS
cmEgressCOS.description: This allows specification of the COS Priority, i.e. this helps in determining the appropriate COS Policer for the Flow.

cmEgressOuterTagCtrl.name: cmEgressOuterTagCtrl
cmEgressOuterTagCtrl.description: This object defines the behavior of the Priority portion of the frame transmit out. If NONE is selected, the outgoing priority bits are left unchanged. If SWAP is selected, the priority bits are changed by the value specified in the Outer-Tag Priority parameter.

cmEgressOuterTagPriority.description: This object defines the new priority bits to be used, it is available only if Outer-Tag PRIOCTL is set to SWAP.

cmQosPolicerProfileCouplingFlag.name: cmQosPolicerProfileCouplingFlag
cmQosPolicerProfileCouplingFlag.description: This object allows specification of Policer Coupling Flag. When coupling is enabled, tokens that would normally be added to the C-bucket are passed to the E-bucket only once the CIR bucket has reached its CBS level. Therefore under this condition the E-bucket is being filled at the rate of CIR + EIR. Normally the long term average of frames declared yellow, which is bounded by the EIR. Coupling is a function to allow the long term average of frames declared yellow to be bounded by CIR + EIR. This allows a higher volume of yellow frames to be delivered/received if the arrival of green marked frames is low. Tokens from the E-bucket do NOT get passed to the C-bucket once the EBS level has been reached. Enabling coupling in combination with a provisioned EIR of 0 allows for a single rate three color marking (srTCM) algorithm to be established. In this situation the E-bucket is filled at the CIR rate in the case the C-bucket is filled to its CBS level.

ocnStmBerDegThreshold.name: ocnStmBerDegThreshold
ocnStmBerDegThreshold.description: This object provides the threshold of B2DEG.

ocnStmExpectedTrailTrace.name: ocnStmExpectedTrailTrace

ocnStmQLModeEnabled.name: ocnStmQLModeEnabled
ocnStmQLModeEnabled.description: This object allows to specify whether the OCn/STM interface can be enabled/disabled for QL Mode. This object is only applicable for Synchronous OCn/STM interface, when ocnStmQLModeEnabled is set to true. When enabled, on receive side -port shall PEER the SSM (Sync Status Messages) slow protocol PDUs and take appropriate action When enabled, on transmit side -port shall periodically (once a second) transmit QL TLV information PDUs When disabled, on receive side, -port shall terminate and discard any SSM slow protocol PDUs When disabled, on transmit side -port shall not transmit any SSM slow protocol PDUs.

ocnStmExpectedQL.name: ocnStmExpectedQL
ocnStmExpectedQL.description: This object allows to specify the expected QL when the OCn/STM interface is enabled for QL Mode. This object is only applicable for Synchronous OCn/STM interface, when ocnStmQLModeEnabled is set to true. This object allows the user to set a minimum expected received Quality Level on the port. The valid values depend upon the SYNC entity Network Clock Type. A value of None represents that a minimum Quality Level is not expected. The default value shall be None.

ocnStmAssumedQL.name: ocnStmAssumedQL
ocnStmAssumedQL.description: This object allows to specify the assumed QL on the OCn/STM interface. This object is only applicable for Synchronous OCn/STM interface. The Assumed QL is only meaningful if the Network Clock Type (see fsp150cm-sync.mib) is option1 and the port TransmitQL Mode is disabled and the port is being used as an input reference source. Under these conditions, the specified QL value is assumed to be the Quality Level of the non-failed reference.

ocnStmReceivedQL.name: ocnStmReceivedQL
ocnStmReceivedQL.description: This object provides the Received QL value for the OCn/STM interface. If the OCn/STM interface TransmitQL Mode is disabled, then the received QL value is not applicable.This object is only applicable for Synchronous OCn/STM interface.

ocnStmTransmitQL.name: ocnStmTransmitQL
ocnStmTransmitQL.description: This object provides the Transmitted QL value for the OCn/STM interface. If the OCn/STM interface TransmitQL Mode is disabled, then the received QL value is not applicable. This object is only applicable for Synchronous OCn/STM interface.

ocnStmPortType.name: ocnStmPortType
ocnStmPortType.description: This object represents the OCN/STM Port Type. Determines whether the OCN/STM port operates in OC or STM mode.

ocnStmFreqSourceType.name: ocnStmFreqSourceType

In the case when parent of E1T1Entry does not have a InterfaceIndex then the e1t1ParentIfIndex shall have the value of 2147483647, e.g. if parent of E1T1Entry is a card represented in pseudoWireE1T1CardTable.

e1t1RowStatus.description: The status of this row. Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The e1t1RowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

e1t1LineType.name: e1t1LineType
e1t1LineType.description: This object represents the E1/T1 Line Type. Determines whether the E1/T1 interface operates in T1 or E1 mode.

e1t1LineCode.name: e1t1LineCode
e1t1LineCode.description: This object represents the E1/T1 Port Line Code. When the port is configured for a Line Type of T1, the valid values are t1-b8zs and t1-ami and the default value is t1-b8zs. When the port is configured for a Line Type of E1, the valid values are e1-hdb3 and e1-ami and the default value is e1-hdb3.

e1t1FrameFormat.name: e1t1FrameFormat
e1t1FrameFormat.description: This object represents the E1/T1 Port Frame Format. When the port is configured for a Line Type of T1, the valid values are t1-sf, t1-esf and t1-unframed and the default value is t1-unframed. When the port is configured for a Line Type of E1, the valid values are e1-unframed, e1-crc4, and e1-dualFrame and the default value is e1-crc4. R5.4CC supports only t1-unframed for T1 Line type.

e1t1LineBuildOut.name: e1t1LineBuildOut
e1t1LineBuildOut.description: This object represents Line Build Out on E1/T1 port.

e1t1TimingDomain.name: e1t1TimingDomain
e1t1TimingDomain.description: This object represents Timing Domain that the E1/T1 interface uses as timing source. The Timing Domain is a Synchronization Entity represented by an object in the f3SyncTable

e1t1RcvSensitivity.name: e1t1RcvSensitivity
e1t1RcvSensitivity.description: This object allows configuring the reciever sensitivity based on expected signal strength

e1t1IdlePatternProfile.name: e1t1IdlePatternProfile

e1t1LoopbackProfile.name: e1t1LoopbackProfile
e1t1LoopbackProfile.description: This object allows selecting Loopback Profile for the E1/T1 interface. Loopback Profile is represented by an object in the f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileTable
