cmEthernetTrafficPortTDMEncapsulation.description: This object describes the GFP Encapsulation type of the traffic port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortRelatedVCG.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortRelatedVCG
cmEthernetTrafficPortRelatedVCG.description: This object describes the related VCG of the traffic port.

f3PulsePerSecondPortTable.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortTable
f3PulsePerSecondPortTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Pulse Per Second Port Facilities.

f3PulsePerSecondPortEntry.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortEntry
f3PulsePerSecondPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3PulsePerSecondPortTable.

f3PulsePerSecondPortIndex.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortIndex
f3PulsePerSecondPortIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Pulse Per Second Port within the card.

f3PulsePerSecondPortIfIndex.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortIfIndex
f3PulsePerSecondPortIfIndex.description: This object has the same value as ifIndex for Pulse Per Second Port. An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Pulse Per Second Port.

f3PulsePerSecondPortEntityIndex.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortEntityIndex
f3PulsePerSecondPortEntityIndex.description: Entity Index from ENTITY-MIB for this port.

f3PulsePerSecondPortAdminState.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortAdminState
f3PulsePerSecondPortAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Pulse Per Second Port.

f3PulsePerSecondPortOperationalState.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortOperationalState
f3PulsePerSecondPortOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Pulse Per Second Port.

f3PulsePerSecondPortSecondaryState.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortSecondaryState
f3PulsePerSecondPortSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the Pulse Per Second Port.

f3PulsePerSecondPortSquelchControl.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortSquelchControl
f3PulsePerSecondPortSquelchControl.description: This object allows to set the Squelch Control for the Pulse Per Second port. The Squelch Control is used to determine the type of squelch control used to squelch the output of the TOD port.

f3PulsePerSecondPortSquelchQL.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortSquelchQL
f3PulsePerSecondPortSquelchQL.description: This object allows to set the Squelch QL for the Pulse Per Second port. This value is used when f3PulsePerSecondPortSquelchControl is squelch-ql. The Squelch QL is used to determine whether or not to squelch the output of the TOD port. If the system's QL is lower than the Squelch QL, the output is squelched.

f3PulsePerSecondPortTODSource.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortTODSource
f3PulsePerSecondPortTODSource.description: This object allows to set the Pulse Per Second Source for the Port.

f3PulsePerSecondPortDirection.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortDirection
f3PulsePerSecondPortDirection.description: This object allows specification of the signal type (i.e. input or output).

f3PulsePerSecondPortInputRate.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortInputRate
f3PulsePerSecondPortInputRate.description: This object allows specification of the PPS Input Rate.

f3PulsePerSecondPortDelayCompensation.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortDelayCompensation
f3PulsePerSecondPortDelayCompensation.description: This object allows specification of the PPS external Delay Compensation in nanoseconds. The valid values are 0 to 96 in 8 nanoseconds steps. Values which are not multiple of 8 will be automatically rounded up to the next multiple of 8.

f3PulsePerSecondPortClockClass.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortClockClass
f3PulsePerSecondPortClockClass.description: This object specify PPS port clock class.

f3PulsePerSecondPortClockAccuracy.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortClockAccuracy
f3PulsePerSecondPortClockAccuracy.description: This object specify PPS port clock accuracy.

f3PulsePerSecondPortTimeSource.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortTimeSource
f3PulsePerSecondPortTimeSource.description: This object specify PPS port time source.

f3PulsePerSecondPortPhyInterfaceType.name: f3PulsePerSecondPortPhyInterfaceType
f3PulsePerSecondPortPhyInterfaceType.description: This object specify PPS physical interface type.

f3TimeOfDayPortTable.name: f3TimeOfDayPortTable
f3TimeOfDayPortTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Time Of Day Port Facilities.

f3TimeOfDayPortEntry.name: f3TimeOfDayPortEntry
f3TimeOfDayPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3TimeOfDayPortTable.

f3TimeOfDayPortIndex.name: f3TimeOfDayPortIndex
f3TimeOfDayPortIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Time Of Day Port within the card.

f3TimeOfDayPortIfIndex.name: f3TimeOfDayPortIfIndex
f3TimeOfDayPortIfIndex.description: This object has the same value as ifIndex for Time Of Day Port. An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Time Of Day Port.

f3TimeOfDayPortEntityIndex.name: f3TimeOfDayPortEntityIndex
f3TimeOfDayPortEntityIndex.description: Entity Index from ENTITY-MIB for this port.

f3TimeOfDayPortAdminState.name: f3TimeOfDayPortAdminState
f3TimeOfDayPortAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Time Of Day Port.

f3TimeOfDayPortOperationalState.name: f3TimeOfDayPortOperationalState
f3TimeOfDayPortOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Time Of Day Port.

f3TimeOfDayPortSecondaryState.name: f3TimeOfDayPortSecondaryState
f3TimeOfDayPortSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the Time Of Day Port.

f3TimeOfDayPortSquelchControl.name: f3TimeOfDayPortSquelchControl
f3TimeOfDayPortSquelchControl.description: This object allows to set the Squelch Control for the Time Of Day port. The Squelch Control is used to determine the type of squelch control used to squelch the output of the TOD port.

f3TimeOfDayPortSquelchQL.name: f3TimeOfDayPortSquelchQL
f3TimeOfDayPortSquelchQL.description: This object allows to set the Squelch QL for the Time Of Day port. This value is used when f3TimeOfDayPortSquelchControl is squelch-ql. The Squelch QL is used to determine whether or not to squelch the output of the TOD port. If the system's QL is lower than the Squelch QL, the output is squelched.

f3TimeOfDayPortTODSource.name: f3TimeOfDayPortTODSource
f3TimeOfDayPortTODSource.description: This object allows to set the Time Of Day Source for the Port.

cmEthernetNetPortExtTable.name: cmEthernetNetPortExtTable
cmEthernetNetPortExtTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Network Port Facilities for configuration purposes.

cmEthernetNetPortExtEntry.name: cmEthernetNetPortExtEntry
cmEthernetNetPortExtEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetNetPortExtTable.

cmEthernetNetPortTDMEncapsulation.name: cmEthernetNetPortTDMEncapsulation
cmEthernetNetPortTDMEncapsulation.description: This object describes the GFP Encapsulation type of the TDM network port.

cmEthernetNetPortAssociatedTdmEntity.name: cmEthernetNetPortAssociatedTdmEntity
cmEthernetNetPortAssociatedTdmEntity.description: This object describes the associated working path of TDM network port.

cmEthernetNetPortInsertingAIS.name: cmEthernetNetPortInsertingAIS
cmEthernetNetPortInsertingAIS.description: This object allows to insert AIS out from TDM network port when it is in maintenance state.

f3GPSReceiverPortTable.name: f3GPSReceiverPortTable
f3GPSReceiverPortTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the GPS Receiver Port Facilities.

f3GPSReceiverPortEntry.name: f3GPSReceiverPortEntry
f3GPSReceiverPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3GPSReceiverPortTable.

f3GPSReceiverPortIndex.name: f3GPSReceiverPortIndex
f3GPSReceiverPortIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this GPS Receiver Port within the card.

f3GPSReceiverPortIfIndex.name: f3GPSReceiverPortIfIndex
f3GPSReceiverPortIfIndex.description: This object has the same value as ifIndex for Time Of Day Port. An integer index value used to uniquely identify this GPS Receiver Port.

f3GPSReceiverPortEntityIndex.name: f3GPSReceiverPortEntityIndex
f3GPSReceiverPortEntityIndex.description: Entity Index from ENTITY-MIB for this port.

f3GPSReceiverPortAdminState.name: f3GPSReceiverPortAdminState
f3GPSReceiverPortAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the GPS Receiver Port.

f3GPSReceiverPortOperationalState.name: f3GPSReceiverPortOperationalState
f3GPSReceiverPortOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the GPS Receiver Port.

f3GPSReceiverPortSecondaryState.name: f3GPSReceiverPortSecondaryState
f3GPSReceiverPortSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the GPS Receiver Port.

f3GPSReceiverPortPPSGenCondition.name: f3GPSReceiverPortPPSGenCondition
f3GPSReceiverPortPPSGenCondition.description: This object allows for configuration of the PPS generation condition. PPS is generated when at least one satellite is tracked or when at least three satellites are tracked.

f3GPSReceiverPortAntennaCableLength.name: f3GPSReceiverPortAntennaCableLength
f3GPSReceiverPortAntennaCableLength.description: This object allows for configuration of the GPS Antenna cable length in meters.

f3GPSReceiverPortAntennaStatus.name: f3GPSReceiverPortAntennaStatus
f3GPSReceiverPortAntennaStatus.description: This object provides the GPS Receiver Port Antenna status.

f3GPSReceiverPortSatellitesUsableFlag.name: f3GPSReceiverPortSatellitesUsableFlag
f3GPSReceiverPortSatellitesUsableFlag.description: This object provides information on whether the satellites are usable. It is set to TRUE, when ephemeris and health data for at least one satellite is available.

f3GPSReceiverPortNumTrackingSatellites.name: f3GPSReceiverPortNumTrackingSatellites
f3GPSReceiverPortNumTrackingSatellites.description: This object provides information on the number of tracking satellites.

f3GPSReceiverPortSelfSurveyProgress.name: f3GPSReceiverPortSelfSurveyProgress
f3GPSReceiverPortSelfSurveyProgress.description: This object provides information on the percentage of fixes collected so far.

f3GPSReceiverPortPPSGeneratedFlag.name: f3GPSReceiverPortPPSGeneratedFlag
f3GPSReceiverPortPPSGeneratedFlag.description: This object indicates whether there are enough usable satellites to provide accurate PPS output.

f3GPSReceiverPortGnssSystem.name: f3GPSReceiverPortGnssSystem
f3GPSReceiverPortGnssSystem.description: This object configure Constellation Type of the GPS Antenna.

f3GPSReceiverPortInstallationType.name: f3GPSReceiverPortInstallationType
f3GPSReceiverPortInstallationType.description: This object configure Installation Type of the GPS Antenna.

f3GPSReceiverPortGnssTOD.name: f3GPSReceiverPortGnssTOD
f3GPSReceiverPortGnssTOD.description: This object provides the last time was executed.

f3GPSReceiverPortGnssSystemsBitMap.name: f3GPSReceiverPortGnssSystemsBitMap
f3GPSReceiverPortGnssSystemsBitMap.description: this object configures GNSS constellation types supported by a GNSS Receiver Port

f3GPSReceiverPortAlias.name: f3GPSReceiverPortAlias
f3GPSReceiverPortAlias.description: This object provides an alias to the GPS port

cmPethPsePortExtTable.name: cmPethPsePortExtTable
cmPethPsePortExtTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to PsePortExtEntry.

cmPethPsePortExtEntry.name: cmPethPsePortExtEntry
cmPethPsePortExtEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmPethPsePortExtEntry.

cmPethPsePortExtGroupIndex.name: cmPethPsePortExtGroupIndex
cmPethPsePortExtGroupIndex.description: This object has the same value with the group index in pethPsePortTalbe.

cmPethPsePortExtIndex.name: cmPethPsePortExtIndex
cmPethPsePortExtIndex.description: This object has the same value with the port index in pethPsePortTalbe.

cmPethPsePortExtAssociatedPort.name: cmPethPsePortExtAssociatedPort
cmPethPsePortExtAssociatedPort.description: This object means the oid of associated physical port.

pethPsePortExtPowerConsumption.name: pethPsePortExtPowerConsumption
pethPsePortExtPowerConsumption.description: This object means the power consumption of each port in mWatts.

pethPsePortExtAvailablePowerLevel.name: pethPsePortExtAvailablePowerLevel
pethPsePortExtAvailablePowerLevel.description: This object means the pse port available power level.

pethMainPseEXTTable.name: pethMainPseEXTTable
pethMainPseEXTTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to PethMainPseEXTEntry.

pethMainPseEXTEntry.name: pethMainPseEXTEntry
pethMainPseEXTEntry.description: A conceptual row in the pethMainPseEXTEntry.

pethMainPseExtGroupIndex.name: pethMainPseExtGroupIndex
pethMainPseExtGroupIndex.description: This object has the same value with the group index in pethMainPseEXTTable.

pethMainPseExtNonStandardPD.name: pethMainPseExtNonStandardPD
pethMainPseExtNonStandardPD.description: disabled: don't support non-standard PD, enabled: support non-standard PD

cmMPFlowTable.name: cmMPFlowTable
cmMPFlowTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to MPFlow.

cmMPFlowEntry.name: cmMPFlowEntry
cmMPFlowEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmMPFlowTable.

cmMPFlowIndex.name: cmMPFlowIndex
cmMPFlowIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this MultiPointFlow.

cmMPFlowCircuitName.name: cmMPFlowCircuitName
cmMPFlowCircuitName.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide a circuit identifier with the MPFlow.

cmMPFlowAdminState.name: cmMPFlowAdminState
cmMPFlowAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Flow.

cmMPFlowOperationalState.name: cmMPFlowOperationalState
cmMPFlowOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Flow.

cmMPFlowSecondaryState.name: cmMPFlowSecondaryState
cmMPFlowSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the Flow.

cmMPFlowLearningEnabled.name: cmMPFlowLearningEnabled
cmMPFlowLearningEnabled.description: DISABLED: The forwarding function of the Flow does not dynamically learn MAC address to flowpoint mapping. ENABLED: The forwarding function of the Flow dynamically learns MAC address to flowpoint mapping based on ingress flowpoing and source MAC address.

cmMPFlowAgingTimer.name: cmMPFlowAgingTimer
cmMPFlowAgingTimer.description: MAC Table Entry will be removed from the forwarding table after an inactivity time represented by this entry. Not used in EG-X.

cmMPFlowFwdTableSizeProfileID.name: cmMPFlowFwdTableSizeProfileID
cmMPFlowFwdTableSizeProfileID.description: Profile ID for Maximum number of MAC Table Entries for the flow

cmMPFlowtableFullAction.name: cmMPFlowtableFullAction
cmMPFlowtableFullAction.description: Action on ingress frames when the number of MAC Table entires has reached the maximum defined by tableSize. BLOCK: A frame with a Source MAC address not in the MAC Table will be discarded. FORWARD: A frame with a Source MAC address not in the MAC table will not be learned and will be flooded to other flowpoints.

cmMPFlowStorageType.name: cmMPFlowStorageType
cmMPFlowStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmMPFlowRowStatus.name: cmMPFlowRowStatus
cmMPFlowRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cmMPFlowRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with cmFlowRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cmMPFlowRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1). Note that flow creation and deletion is only supported with access port in connection-oriented evpl mode.

cmMPFlowLearningConfigAction.name: cmMPFlowLearningConfigAction
cmMPFlowLearningConfigAction.description: This objects allows performing user action on Learning Table.

cmMPFlowFPList.name: cmMPFlowFPList
cmMPFlowFPList.description: This object only used to display trap and Flow point list. Fp will be add in the cmMPFlowMemberTable.

cmMPFlowMemberTable.name: cmMPFlowMemberTable
cmMPFlowMemberTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to MPFlowMember.

cmMPFlowMemberEntry.name: cmMPFlowMemberEntry
cmMPFlowMemberEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmMPFlowMemberTable.

cmMPFlowMemberFPIndex.name: cmMPFlowMemberFPIndex
cmMPFlowMemberFPIndex.description: This object describes the relate Flow point.

cmMPFlowPointRowStatus.name: cmMPFlowPointRowStatus
cmMPFlowPointRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cmMPFlowPointRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with cmFlowRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cmMPFlowPointRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1). Note that flow creation and deletion is only supported with access port in connection-oriented evpl mode.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncTable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncTable
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncTable.description: EthernetTraffic Port PCP drop eligibility encoding table. This is applied to a frame that is egressing at the EthernetTraffic port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncEntry.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncEntry
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncEntry.description: A conceptual row in the ethernetPBPcpDEEncPortTable.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncIndex.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncIndex
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a row in the PCP drop eligible encoding table.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncInPriority.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncInPriority
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncInPriority.description: This object is the input priority that is translated to a drop eligibility priority or a drop ineligibility priority.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncDropIneligi.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncDropIneligiblePrio
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncDropIneligi.description: This object is the PCP value that has a priority value with implicit drop ineligibility encoded into it.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncDropEligibl.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncDropEligiblePrio
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEEncDropEligibl.description: This object is the PCP value that has a priority value with implicit drop eligibility encoded into it.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecTable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecTable
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecTable.description: EthernetTraffic Port PCP drop eligibility decoding table. This is applied to a frame that is ingressing at a port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecEntry.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecEntry
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecEntry.description: A conceptual row in the ethernetPBPcpDEDecPortTable.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecIndex.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecIndex
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a row in the PCP drop eligible decoding table.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecInPriority.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecInPriority
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecInPriority.description: This object is the input priority that is decoded to get priority and the drop eligibility of a frame.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecOutPriority.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecOutPriority
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecOutPriority.description: This object is the priority value decoded from a incoming PCP value.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecDropEligibl.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecDropEligible
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDecDropEligibl.description: This object is the drop eligibility decoded from a incoming PCP value.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairTable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairTable
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairTable.description: EthernetTraffic Port PCP drop eligibility priority pair table. The priority pair is encoded to same drop eligibility and drop ineligibility priority. Depending on the PCP DE Enc/Dec mode there can be upto 3 pairs in the table. There will one pair for 7P1D, two pairs for 6P2D and three pairs for 5P3D.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairEntry.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairEntry
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmAccPortPcpDEPairEntry.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairIndex.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairIndex
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEPairIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a row in the PCP drop eligible priority pair table.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDropIneligible.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDropIneligiblePrio
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDropIneligible.description: This object is the drop ineligible priority.

cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDropEligiblePr.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDropEligiblePrio
cmEthernetTrafficPortPcpDEDropEligiblePr.description: This object is the drop eligible priority.

cmEthernetTrafficPortClbTable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortClbTable
cmEthernetTrafficPortClbTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Traffic Port Cable Length Benchmark.

cmEthernetTrafficPortClbEntry.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortClbEntry
cmEthernetTrafficPortClbEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetTrafficPortClbTable. These entries represent Cable Length Benchmarks on the Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortClbIndex.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortClbIndex
cmEthernetTrafficPortClbIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Cable Length Benchmark Entry specification.

cmEthernetTrafficPortClbEnabled.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortClbEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortClbEnabled.description: This enables specification of Cable Length Benchmark entry.

cmEthernetTrafficPortClbLength.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortClbLength
cmEthernetTrafficPortClbLength.description: Cable length of Cable Points Entry. The cable length is of the form XXX[.YY] where XX can be any integer value and YY allows precision of 2 decimals after the floating point. Note that .YY is optional.

cmEthernetTrafficPortClbDescr.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortClbDescr
cmEthernetTrafficPortClbDescr.description: A textual string containing description of cable span.

networkElementTMParamsTable.name: networkElementTMParamsTable
networkElementTMParamsTable.description: Entries may be auto discovered, or can be explicitly created by SNMP Manager. Each remotely discovered shelf is represented as a row in this table.

networkElementTMParamsEntry.name: networkElementTMParamsEntry
networkElementTMParamsEntry.description: A conceptual row in the networkElementTMParamsTable.

neTMParamsBandwidthProfileMode.name: neTMParamsBandwidthProfileMode
neTMParamsBandwidthProfileMode.description: A Network Element level Bandwidth Profile Mode shall be supported which will indicate if the CIR/EIR is interpreted as Information Rate (IR) or Line Rate (LR). In IR mode BWP is enforced based on number of bytes beginning with DA and ending with FCS as it was received at a port which is called the Service Frame in MEF terminology. In LR mode the BWP is enforced based on the whole frame including IFG, Preamble and SFD.

neTMParamsAgingtime.name: neTMParamsAgingtime
neTMParamsAgingtime.description: The object describe the system aging time.

cmEthernetAccPortJdsuExtTable.name: cmEthernetAccPortJdsuExtTable
cmEthernetAccPortJdsuExtTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Access Port Facilities for JDSU configuration purposes.

cmEthernetAccPortJdsuExtEntry.name: cmEthernetAccPortJdsuExtEntry
cmEthernetAccPortJdsuExtEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetAccPortJdsuExtTable.

cmEthernetAccPortJDSUControlFramesSnoopi.name: cmEthernetAccPortJDSUControlFramesSnoopingEnabled
cmEthernetAccPortJDSUControlFramesSnoopi.description: Enabled: reaction/response to JDSU in-band loopback requests and hallo requests. Disabled: Not reaction/response to JDSU in-band loopback requests and hallo requests. FPGA shall not filter the JDSU control frames to processor. From enabled to disabled, if there is already a JDSU loopback on the port, release current loopback. JDSU loopback doesn't need port in maintenance state.

cmEthernetAccPortJDSULoopbackVlan.name: cmEthernetAccPortJDSULoopbackVlan
cmEthernetAccPortJDSULoopbackVlan.description: Applicable when port in JDSU VLAN loopback.

cmEthernetNetPortJdsuExtTable.name: cmEthernetNetPortJdsuExtTable
cmEthernetNetPortJdsuExtTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Ethernet Network Port Facilities for JDSU configuration purposes.

cmEthernetNetPortJdsuExtEntry.name: cmEthernetNetPortJdsuExtEntry
cmEthernetNetPortJdsuExtEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetNetPortJdsuExtTable.

cmEthernetNetPortJDSUControlFramesSnoopi.name: cmEthernetNetPortJDSUControlFramesSnoopingEnabled
cmEthernetNetPortJDSUControlFramesSnoopi.description: Enabled: reaction/response to JDSU in-band loopback requests and hallo requests. Disabled: Not reaction/response to JDSU in-band loopback requests and hallo requests. FPGA shall not filter the JDSU control frames to processor. From enabled to disabled, if there is already a JDSU loopback on the port, release current loopback. JDSU loopback doesn't need port in maintenance state.

cmEthernetNetPortJDSULoopbackVlan.name: cmEthernetNetPortJDSULoopbackVlan
cmEthernetNetPortJDSULoopbackVlan.description: Applicable when port in JDSU VLAN loopback.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkTable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkTable
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Vlan loopback on Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkEntry.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkEntry
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkTable. These entries represent Vlan loopback on the Ethernet Traffic Port.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkIndex.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkIndex
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this vlan loopback entry.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkInnerVlanEnable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkInnerVlanEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkInnerVlanEnable.description: This object represent the inner vlan whether enabled.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkInnerVlanTag.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkInnerVlanTag
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkInnerVlanTag.description: This object represent the inner vlanid value and priority value. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkOuterVlanEnable.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkOuterVlanEnabled
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkOuterVlanEnable.description: This object represent the outter vlan whether enabled.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkOuterVlanTag.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkOuterVlanTag
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkOuterVlanTag.description: This object represent the outter vlanid value and priority value. The value to be specified should be in the form X-Y where X is the VLAN Id and Y is the VLAN Priority. If Y is specified as a *, all Priorities (0 to 7) are looped back.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkTime.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkTime
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkTime.description: This object represent the vlan loopback time.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkStatus.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkStatus
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkStatus.description: This object represent the vlan loopback status.

cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkConfig.name: cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkConfig
cmEthernetTrafficPortLpbkConfig.description: This object represent the vlan loopback action.

An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object.
